(3290, 0, 0, 1, 'ELS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Saša Vučičević', 1, 'Analiza karakteristika semi-bridgeless PFC ispravljača sa izlaznom snagom preko 4 kW', 'popravka faktora snage; PFC; Interleaved PFC; Bridgeless PFC; Semi-Bridgeless PFC; upravljačko kolo UCC28070; modul tranzistor-dioda; efikasnost kola za popravku faktora snage; elektromagnetne smetnje.', 'U radu je opisan ispravljač sa popravkom faktora snage (Power factor correction - PFC) sa dva podizača (DC/DC pretvarača), takozvani interleaved ispravljač, i to njegova bridgeless konfiguracija, gdje se koriste samo dvije diode mosnog ispravljača, radi smanjenja gubitaka. Konstruisan je PFC velike izlazne snage (preko 4 kW), sa dobrom efikasnošću (i do 97%) i dobrim faktorom snage (preko 0,9). Koristilo se upravljačko kolo UCC28070, kao i modul tranzistor-dioda APT50N60JCCU2. Testiranja su rađena na standardnim mrežnim naponima od 230 Vac i 115 Vac.  U radu su prikazani rezultati testiranja ovakvog ispravljača: efikasnost, faktor snage, sadržaj viših harmonika, kao i rezultati testiranja na elektromagnetne smetnje.'),
(3291, 1, 0, 1, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mladen Knezic', 1, 'Towards Implementation of Frame Preemption Mechanism on FPGA Platform', 'audio video bridging; ethernet; frame preemption; FPGA; time sensitive networking; VHDL', 'Time Sensitive Networking (TSN) becomes a dominant technology, both in automotive networks and industrial communication systems. Recent amendments to IEEE 802.1 and 802.3 standards, delivered by several TSN working groups, allowed for deterministic and synchronized communication on top of Ethernet infrastructure. One such amendment introduces a frame preemption mechanism, which enables low-priority traffic to be interrupted by time-critical frames of higher priority. In this paper, we describe an implementation of the frame preemption mechanism on a low-cost FPGA (Field-Programmable Gate Array) platform. The functionality of the implemented design has been verified using industry standard tools and the verification results are reported in the paper.'),
(3292, 0, 0, 3, 'ELS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nikola Kukrić', 1, 'Sistem za nadzor mikroklime u plastenicima', 'nadzor mikroklime; senzorska očitanja; microkontroler; senzorski čvor;', 'Nadzor mikroklime u plastenicima može znatno doprinijeti prinosu biljaka po jedinici površine zemlje. U tom cilju, potrebno je imati nadzorni sistem za praćenje vrijednosti parametara zraka i zemljišta, koji bitno utiču na razvoj pojedinih agrikultura u plasteniku. U ovom radu opisan je sistem za prikupljanje podataka, te njihovo pohranjivanje. Zbog povećanja dimenzija plastenika, na sisteme za nadzor mikroklime postavljaju se dodatni zahtjevi, a jedan od ključnih je potreba da se na više tačaka u plasteniku mjere pojedini parametri. Zbog toga je razvijen bežični sistem za nadzor mikroklime koji omogućava komunikaciju većeg broja mjernih jedinica, čuvanje podataka na serveru, obradu i analizu dobijenih podataka te tabelarni i grafički prikaz istih na web stranici. Jedan od ključnih zahtjeva je niska potrošnja, te je potrebno obratiti pažnju na odabir senzora, protokola za komunikaciju i mikrokontrolera sa ciljem što manje potrošnje a zadržavajući autentičnost podataka.'),
(3293, 0, 0, 4, 'ELS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nenad Jovančić', 1, 'Pražnjači akumulatorskih baterija – efikasna metoda za potpuno pražnjenje baterija kontrolisanom strujom', 'baterija, pražnjači baterija, potpuno pražnjenje, reciklaža baterija', 'Baterije se najčešće koriste kod potrošača koji u svakom trenutku trebaju napajanje – elementi kontrole i zaštite vitalnih dijelova elektroenergetske mreže, serveri velikih bankarskih sistema, medicinska oprema u urgentnim odjeljenjima i mnogi drugi. Da bi se očuvala pouzdanost baterija, vrši se njihov stalni nadzor i periodično ispitivanje. Između ostalog, vrši se kontrolisano pražnjenje u cilju određivanja raspoložive energije u njima. Takođe, na kraju životnog vijeka baterije, vrši se njena reciklaža. Kroz istoriju, koristili su se različiti tipovi pražnjača. U novije vrijeme egzistiraju dva tipa - oni koji energiju baterije troše na pasivne terete i oni koji vrše rekuperaciju energije. Istraživanja koja se provode od strane određenih proizvođača Li-ion baterija pokazuju da se postiže veća efikasnost reciklaže ove vrste baterija ako je stepen zaostale energije u njima manji – posebno ako se vrši potpuno pražnjenje. Zbog svoje konstrukcije, klasični pražnjači ne mogu vršiti toliko duboka pražnjenja kontrolisanom strujom. U ovom radu opisana je metoda i predstavljen sistem/uređaj koji može da vrši potpuno pražnjenje baterija kontrolisanom strujom naponskog nivoa do 800 Vdc.'),
(3294, 0, 0, 5, 'ELS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Milan Vesković', 1, 'Precision Full-Wave Rectifier - Practical Realization in Discrete Technology', 'Full-Wave Precision Rectifier; Through Hole; Discrete Elements', 'In this paper is presented practical realization of the full-wave precision rectifier in discrete technology. Full-wave precision rectifier is realized with bipolar transistor with discrete elements on the raster board. PSPICE program was used to verify the proposed design of the full-wave precision rectifier. The results of the simulation are presented and compared with the results of the measurement of the realization that was published.'),
(3295, 0, 0, 6, 'ELS', '2019', 1, 1, 'Mitar Simić', 1, 'Electronic System for Remote Monitoring of Environmental Parameters on a Bee Yard', 'embedded systems; environmental parameters sensors.', 'Although there are plenty of commercial systems dedicated to measuring environmental parameters, because of need for specific parameters of interest (temperature, relative humidity, atmospheric pressure, ultraviolet light level, infrared light level and visible light level, micro-sized particles concentrations, magnetic flux density, and wind speed) we proposed a multi-sensors and low-cost platform designed for remote monitoring of environmental conditions on a bee yard. The proposed system has specific features such as portability, battery-power supply, and unit for transmitting data to the remote server. Initial testing showed ability of the system to process all data on time and to perform reliable acquisition.'),
(3296, 1, 0, 2, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Vesna Miletić', 1, 'Fotoakustička karakterizacija PLLA uzoraka različitih nivoa kristaliničnosti', 'eksperiment; fotoakustika; PLLA; dvoslojni sistem;', 'Specijalno pripremeljeni PLLA uzorci su prekriveni tankim polimernim slojem akrilne boje, formirajući na taj način neprozirni zaštitni sloj. Uniformnost i debljina nanetog sloja su potvrđeni, a onda su izvršena merenja frekventnog fotoakustičkog (FA) odziva dobijenog dvoslojnog sistema korišćenjem FA ćelije minimalne zapremine u transmisionoj konfiguraciji. Ponovljivost je potvrđena višestrukim merenjima na dva nivoa debljine i za svaku stranu pojedinačno. Prikazani rezultati obrađenih merenja potvrđuju ispravnost odluke da se u teorijskom modelovanju odziva i potonjoj interpretaciji koristi dvoslojni generalizovani model FA odziva. Predložene su dalje metode obrade dobijenih podataka, sa ciljem kvantitativne karakterizacije ispitivanog polimernom materijala pomoću procedura zasnovanih na veštačkoj inteligenciji (neuronskim mrežama).'),
(3297, 0, 0, 8, 'ELS', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Spektralna analiza Korotkovih tonova brahijalne arterije prilikom neinvezivne metode mjerenja krvnog pritiska', '1. Korotkov, 2. Spektralna analiza,  3. Ekspres algoritmi LabVIEW-a, 4. Invazivno mjerenje krvnog pritiska, 5.Neinvazivno mjerenje krvnog pritiska, 6. Digitalni stetoskop  ThinkLab ONE', 'Predmet rada je analiza Korotkovih tonova pri rutinskm mjerenju krvnog pritiska, a što predstavlja jednu od osnovnih ljekarskih pregleda. Predložena metoda ne iziskuje bilo kakve značajnije troškove, niti dodatni ljekarski pregled nego se vrši paralelno za vrijeme samog mjerenja krvnog pritiska. Razmatrana su dva načina snimanja Korotkovih tonova. Prva  varijanta je korištenjem digitalnog stetoskopa Thinklabs ONE koji ima jedan poseban audio izlaz za PC, LabTop, tablet ili mobilni telefon, dok se drugi izlaz koristi za klasične medicinske ili profesionalne audio slušalice. Druga varijanta odnosi se na slučaj da ambulanta ne posjeduje navedeni ili slični elektronski stetoskop. U tom slučaju izvršena je jednostavna modifikacija gumene cijevi klasičnog uređaja za mjerenje pritiska. Naime, metalni T komad je ubačen u tu gumenu cijev kao i mikrofon koji se spaja na audio ulaz računara ili LapTop-a. Na taj način je omogućeno automatsko snimanje Korotkovih zvukova kao i njihova spektralna analiza kao i druge analize koje pruža programski paket LabVIEW-a. Na taj način se dobijaju i druge vrlo značajne informacije koje su od izuzetne važnosti za provjeru indeksa čvrstine Karotidne arterije (stifnis index). Osim toga, jednostavnim praćenjem izostatka pojedine faze Korotkovih tonova moguće je dobiti i simptome Systemic Sklerosis [21].'),
(3298, 1, 0, 3, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mirko Stojcic', 1, 'Quality Analysis of Data Transferring Through the Process of Modeling WirelessHART Network', 'WirelessHART; Process industry; Mesh network; Latency signal', 'This research will be analyzed quality of data transferring in WirelessHART network using two network topologies: Extended star network and Mesh network. Quality analysis of data transferring in these network topologies will be provided based on the latency and signal levels. Experimental researches will be carried out using equipment from the manufacturer Emerson Process Management: Gateway 1420, TT 648 and PT 3051 for the implementation of the network, as well as software tools for configuration, planning and management of wireless industrial networks, as follows: AMS Wireless SNAP-ON and AMS Intelligent Device Manager.'),
(3299, 1, 0, 4, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mirko Stojčić', 1, 'Adaptive neuro-fuzzy model for traffic signs recognition', 'ANFIS; traffic sign recognition; model', 'Traffic sign recognition is a very important component of Intelligent Transport Systems (ITS), which today is largely based on the application of artificial intelligence. The aim of this study is to explore the ability to recognize traffic signs from an image using an adaptive neuro-fuzzy inference system (ANFIS) model. To date, much research has been published whose area of concern relates to the recognition of traffic signs. However, the application of the ANFIS model as a possible solution has not been sufficiently explored. The methodology presented in this paper uses the geometric properties of symbols on a traffic sign as input ANFIS variables. It is proposed to develop five independent models that should categorize the represented sign. The final decision is made based on most of the outputs of the ANFIS model, and the method showed a high level of recognition accuracy and adaptability.'),
(3300, 1, 0, 5, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Milica Ristovic Krstic', 1, 'Primjena AD9248  konvertora za prikupljanje podataka o mrežnom naponu', 'FPGA; A/D konverzija; AD konvertor', 'U ovom radu izvedena je praktična realizacija AD konvertora sa integrisanim AD9248 čipom, kojim se upravlja FPGA kolom (eng. Field Programmable Gate Arrays), a gdje se rezultat A/D konverzije prikazuje na osciloskopu. Takođe, data je teorijska osnova kao i konkretna objašnjenja vezana za samu realizaciju. Opisan je korišćeni AD konvertor (AD9248) objašnjen njegov princip rada, a zatim je opisana konkretna realizacija hardvera; prikazana električna šema kao i način povezivanja i upravljačka logika između same kontrolne ploče i AD konvertora. Na kraju je izvršeno testiranju realizovanog AD konvertora.'),
(3301, 1, 0, 6, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Igor Baranovski', 1, 'Support for Self-service Automated Parking Systems', 'Self-service; Automated systems; Parking payment; Smart cities', 'Due to the increasing numbers of cars in cities, organizations of parking zones and fees are crucial to the efficient functioning of traffic in cities. For most urban areas, the number of parking spaces, especially on-street parking, is usually not enough.  On-street parking is the most common form of parking in cities. There are several ways for on-street parking payments such as special parking vouchers, text messages via mobile phones, special smartphone applications, self-service parking machines, and parking meters. Over 95% of the on-street parking in the world is paid by parking meters and self-service parking machines. In order for constant improvement of the parking services, one approach is by extending the functionality of self-service parking machines with the introduction of new technologies. This paper describes the support for on-street parking payment systems, by introducing new parking kiosk (self-service parking machine) that can be easily integrated with other parking payment systems in the cities.'),
(3302, 0, 0, 1, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Tarik Hubana', 1, 'Artificial Intelligence based Station Protection Concept for Medium Voltage Microgrids', 'Microgrids, Power system protection, Artificial neural networks, Discrete wavelet transforms', 'Despite the rapid improvements in the field of microgrid protection, it continues to be one of the most important challenges faced by the distribution system operators. With the introduction of this new operation concept, the existing protection devices are not able to successfully identify, classify and localize different types of faults that occur in the microgrids due to their dynamic behavior, especially in the islanded mode of operation. This paper presents a methodology that provides the station protection functionalities that include detection and classification of faults, isolation of the faulty feeder and fault location estimation. The proposed method is based on discrete wavelet transform and artificial neural networks.  The test system based on the real data, completely developed in MATLAB Simulink, is used to demonstrate the accuracy of all functionalities of the station protection algorithm that can be easily applied in microgrids. The presented results demonstrated the method accuracy and showed that it can be used as an upgrade of the existing protection equipment for the future implementation of the advanced microgrid station protection system.'),
(3303, 0, 0, 2, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Željko V. Despotović', 1, 'SCR Power Converter for Driving of Electromagnetic Vibratory Silo Extractor', 'SCR, power converter, phase control, silo extractor, electromagnetic drive', 'Vibratory extractors are electromechanical devices which provide the flow of the fine-grained or coarse-grained materials, in order to transport them from a silo or storage containers. By meeting the technological requirements of the discharge, these devices contribute significantly to the overall efficiency of the whole extraction system. The vibratory extractor is usually made of a solid two-piece steel structure. The movable part of the vibratory extractor is supported by solid steel coil springs, with a built-in elastic joint. On the moving part there is a drive vibratory device, usually an electromagnetic vibratory actuator which operates with small linear displacements whose vibration intensity and action are adjusted by an SCR power converter. The paper describes the concretely realized solution of SCR power converter and corresponding voltage controller for driving of electromagnetic vibratory extractor, used for extracting of clinkers (semi-finished product in cement production) from the silo. The applied voltage control provides the intensity of clinkers discharge at the output of the silo bunker, and thus the intensity of extractions. The proposed SCR control was verified by experimental results obtained during exploitation. The presented SCR controller was applied in the cement industry.'),
(3304, 0, 0, 3, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Djordje Urukalo', 1, 'Experimental verification of electrical power consumption of resonant electromagnetic vibratory feeder', 'Vibratory feeder, electrical consumption, resonance, process industry', 'Resonant vibratory feeder is the most effective transporting and feeding system of particulate materials that is present in process industry. Resonance effects of such system will allow as high system efficiency, i.e. energy savings for process industry that operate continuously are very high. In paper is presented experimental verification of electrical consumption of one type of resonant electromagnetic vibratory feeder, which is highly represented in process industry. The energy consumption is determined and compared by bringing the feeder into three modes, namely: sub resonant, resonant and super resonant modes. Electromagnetic actuator of vibratory feeder is driven from the asymmetrical half-bridge switch-mode power converter. Measured quantities are: voltage and current of the vibratory actuator and output displacement of trough of the vibratory feeder. It is demonstrated that consumption of the feeder operating in resonance is much lower than of consumption in the sub and super resonance modes. In the paper are shown the key experimental results and based on these results, comments and conclusions was given.'),
(3305, 0, 0, 4, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Milovan Majstorović', 1, 'Implementation of MPPT Methods with SEPIC Converter', 'PV; power conversion; MPPT; P&O; IC; SEPIC', 'Perturb & Observe (P&O) and Incremental Conductance (IC) maximum power point tracking (MPPT) methods are presented in this paper. Algorithms of these methods are implemented in a control of PV-fed single-ended primary inductance converter (SEPIC). These algorithms determine duty cycle of pulse width modulation (PWM) of SEPIC, to control operation point of the system. Power measurements when those methods are applied are then compared to the power measurements for various values of duty cycle, i.e. SEPIC is in open loop, in order to determine efficiency of those methods.'),
(3306, 0, 0, 1, 'ENS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mileta Žarković', 1, 'Mape prioriteta održavanja elektroenergetske opreme na bazi mašinskog učenja', 'plan održavanja; generator; energetski transformator; mašinsko učenje', 'Rad opisuje inovativnu metodologiju formiranja mape prioriteta održavanja ključne elektroenergetske opreme u tehničkim sistemima elektrana. Inovativnost metodologije se ogleda u korišćenju velikih skupova podataka kroz metode mašinskog učenja kako bi se unapredili planovi održavanja prema trenutnom stanju opreme (Condition Based Maintenance–CBM) i prema riziku i pouzdanosti (Reliability Centered Asset Management – RCAM). U radu je razmatran prioritet održavanja 90 generatora i 93 energetska transformatora u proizvodnim jedinicama Elektroprivrede Srbije (EPS). Pri tome su korišćeni veliki skupovi podataka, prikupljeni iz sistemâ monitoringa generatora i transformatora. Na skupovima podataka primenjene su veštačke neuralne mreže iz domena mašinskog učenja. Razvijena metodologija omogućava automatizovano formiranje mapa rizika za potrebe određivanja prioriteta održavanja u elektranama.'),
(3307, 0, 0, 2, 'ENS-1', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Algoritam za proračun kratkih raspona', 'kratak raspon, visokonaponska razvodna postrojenja, sabirnice', 'Ovaj rad nije naučni već inženjerski i opisuje algoritam za rešavanje kratkog raspona koji se na oba kraja završava zateznim izolatorima. Ovakvi rasponi se pojavljuju kod užastih sabirnica u visokonaponskim razvodnim postrojenjima i veoma retko prelaze dužinu od 100m.'),
(3308, 1, 0, 7, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mladen Banjanin', 1, 'Numerical analyses of the selected high voltage electrostatic problems and configurations', 'finite element method; numerical calculations; electrostatic field; high voltage', 'In this paper the FEM-based analyses of the typical high voltage electrostatic problems are presented. Analysed examples are carefully selected to cover some of the fundamental and common configurations and problems in the field of high voltage engineering. Four examples are analysed: impact of the electrodes’ shapes on the electrostatic field intensity and its distribution in the dielectric, impact of the dielectrics’ constants values on the electric field intensity distribution in the double layer insulation system, voltage and electric filed distributions across the long insulator and calculation of the electric field and voltage distribution in the dielectric of the coaxial cable. Presented results and conclusions can be useful both in the students’ education process and for engineers dealing with the high voltage equipment design and testing.'),
(3309, 0, 0, 3, 'ENS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Miljana Todorović', 1, 'The most common failures when setting up a distance protection of the power transmission lines in Bosnia and Herzegovina', 'distance protection; SIR; resistive reach; zero-sequence current compensation factor', 'Distance relay is the main protection of power transmission lines. Incorrect setting of the distance relays may cause unnecessary tripping of transmission lines or extended fault clearing time, which further might jeopardize the power system stability and reliability. The setting principles of distance protection of the power transmission lines in Bosnia and Herzegovina are mainly based on common setting rules for transmission lines. The main irregularities of this setting approach are presented in this paper. Different types of fault that might occur on the transmission lines in Bosnia and Herzegovina, for the different circuit breakers position, are simulated in order to check the adequacy of the distance relay settings. The simulations are performed using PSS CAPE software, specialized in the area of relay protection system simulation.'),
(3310, 0, 0, 9, 'ENS-1', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'DISTRIBUTED GENERATION IN AJK:  A CASE STUDY', 'microgrid; renewable energy; distributed generation; HOMER', 'Renewable energy in today’s biosphere is the last shelter in energy sector. Environmental and social challenges, the world is facing can now be remitted only by using renewable energy sources as a substitute for fossil fuels and other conventional resources. Shockingly, Pakistan is a state where public has reduced access to electricity despite being a basic need, with 38% of the total population having no access to electricity; out of them 54% are from rural areas, compelling them to live a life of social discrimination and scarcity. The multidimensional amphitheater of Pakistani energy sector has made itself a paradox due to which it is facing the increased gap between supply and demand. For decades, fossil fuel and hydel has been and is still functioning as a backbone in electricity supply with an inadequate addition of coal, nuclear based thermal and solar electricity. The basic purpose of this study is to assess and analyze the exploitation of renewable based distributed energy generation in Azad Jammu & Kashmir, an independent state in Pakistan along with state policies. It is proposed that distributed generation based upon renewable energy resources will make country economically strong and help to curtail the energy shortfall.'),
(3311, 0, 0, 10, 'ENS-1', '2019', 1, 1, 'Benjamin Fazlic', 1, 'Benefits and Opportunities of the Wireless Technology Utilization for High Voltage Circuit Breaker and Power Transformer Test Instruments', 'high voltage circuit breaker; power transformers; wireless communication; measurement; data acquisition; instrumentation; condition assessment', 'High-voltage circuit breakers (HVCB), as well as power transformers, as a part of substations, undergo numerous tests during their lifetime. The first test is performed in the factory. The following is the acceptance test performed at a customer site after the delivery. The most numerous are maintenance tests performed during equipment services. All the mentioned tests require an appropriate connection between a test device and a test object, usually utilizing a large number of cables. This can be very time consuming and imposes an additional risk of obtaining appropriate measurement and assessment indices. This paper presents the potential of the wiring replacement by the wireless connection between the test object and test equipment, which would simplify, improve make the test preparation procedure'),
(3312, 0, 0, 5, 'ENS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nikola Miladinović', 1, 'Računarski program za monitoring sadržaja gasova i vode u ulju blok transformatora', 'kontinualni monitoring, računarski program, energetski transformator, sadržaj gasova u ulju transformatora, baza podataka', 'U radu je prikazan računarski program za monitoring sadržaja gasova i vode u ulju blok transformatora. Program je izrađen za potrebe pristupa podacima sa monitoring sistema preko lokalne računarske mreže i uključivanja monitoring sitema u integrisani sistem monitoringa elektroenrgetske opreme elektrane. Program je instaliran na serverskom računaru sistema monitoringa i na industrijskim računarima u ormanima sistema monitoringa na dva agregata. Program vrši akviziciju podataka sa ugrađenih sistema za monitoring sadržaja gasova i vode u ulju transformatora, vizuelni prikaz i arhiviranje u bazu podataka. U okviru programa omogućen je grafički prikaz podataka, arhiviranje svih parametara u relacionu bazu podataka, prikazivanje opomenskih i alarmnih vrednosti parametara, podešavanje granica parametara, izvoz arhiviranih podataka, podešavanje parametara komunikacije sa uređajima za monitoring. Aplikacija je urađena u programskom jeziku Visual C#, a sistem za upravljanje bazama podataka je MySQL. Monitoring sistem je povezan u lokalnu računarsku mrežu hidroelektrane, čime je omogućen pristup inženjerima održavanja elektrane, a putem VPN veze i ekspertima za dijagnostiku stanja transformatora. Na ovaj način se unapređuje procena pogonskog stanja transformatora, povećava mogućnost pravovremenog detektovanja kvarova i drugih anomalija i samim tim povećava pouzdanost i raspoloživost transformatora.'),
(3313, 0, 0, 6, 'ENS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Tomislav Kovač', 1, 'Application of Topology Analysis Results for Fault Location, Isolation and Service Restoration', 'Topology analysis, FLISR, distribution network, bus-branch model', 'Together with technical improvements and innovative solutions in distribution management systems, the standards for reliability and quality of services have been also raised on a higher level. One of the most challenging requirements to accomplish these standards is to minimize the outage impact to the customers by reducing the total interruption time and the number of affected customers. In order to have an efficient response to detected faults, fault location, isolation, and service restoration (FLISR) must be automated to do all required tasks without manual intervention. Topology data and topology functions are a fundamental and indispensable source of information for automated FLISR functions. In this paper is shown how a wide set of topology information provides FLISR functions possibility to have many powerful features that help to reduce interruption duration.'),
(3314, 0, 0, 7, 'ENS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Bozo Ilic', 1, 'Primena modela pametne kuće u nastavi iz predmeta Električne instalacije i Elementi automatizacije', 'Model pametne kuće, Električne instalacije, Elementi automatizacije.', 'Cilj ovog rada jeste da prikaže mogućnosti primene modela pamentne kuće kao nastavnog sredstva u nastavi iz predmeta Električna instalacija i Elementi automatizacije u srednjim i visokim školama, kao i na fakultetima.'),
(3315, 0, 0, 5, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Dario Javor', 1, 'Two-Steps Procedure in Demand Side Management for Reducing Energy Costs', 'demand side management; energy costs; energy efficiency; optimization', 'This paper presents two-steps procedure which can be used in demand side management for reducing energy costs. In the first step of the procedure, values of the maximum and minimum power demands are determined by minimization of the differences between power demands per hour in a daily schedule. In this step is possible to change the time intervals of using a few deferrable loads. In the second step, these values are taken as constraints and the energy costs function is minimized based on the buying prices per hour, thus resulting in the optimized time intervals for using deferrable loads. The optimization is done in program Lingo.'),
(3316, 0, 0, 6, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Predrag Mršić', 1, 'Izbor optimalne pozicije riklozera u srednjenaponskim distributivnim mrežama u prisustvu nesigurnosti podataka', 'riklozer, pokazatelji pouzdanosti, distributivna mreža, Monte Carlo metoda', 'U radu je prezentovan metod za izbor optimalnih lokacija riklozera u srednjenaponskim (SN) distributivnim mrežama. Izbor optimalnih lokacija se vrši tako da vrednosti pokazatelja pouzdanosti SN distributivne mreže budu poboljšani. Kriterijumska funkcija na osnovu koje je izvršen izbor optimalnih lokacija riklozera uzima u obzir srednju učestanost nastanka prekida napajanja, srednje kumulativno vrijeme trajanja prekida napajanja i prosječnu neisporučenu električnu energiju po potrošaču. Prilikom proračuna navedenih pokazatelja pouzdanosti uvažena je nesigurnost podataka. Metoda je prezentovana na IEEE test mreži sa 33 čvora.'),
(3317, 0, 0, 7, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Дарко Шошић', 1, 'Обједињена анализа електроенергетске и мреже даљинског система грејања', 'прорачун токова снага; хидраулично–термички прорачун', 'Енергетски систем на нивоу града са временом постаје све сложенији и разноликији. Различити носиоци енергије међусобно су повезани ради испуњавања различитих енергетских потреба. Уобичајени начин распрегнуте анализе енергетских мрежа не одсликава праву природу заједничког рада енергетског система. Као пример повезаних система може да послужи систем даљинског грејања и електро дистрибутивне мреже. Везу између ова два система могу да представљају CHP јединице, топлотне пумпе и електрични бојлери. У овом раду је приказан декомпоновани електро хидро–термални прорачун.'),
(3318, 1, 0, 8, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Olena  Rubanenko', 1, 'Determination of Normative Value Power Losses in Distribution power grids with Renewable Energy Sources using Criterion Method', 'power grids, substations, distrubuted power generation, power control, renewable energy sources', 'The paper presents the possibility of using criterion programming and neuro-fuzzy modeling in determining the value of planning technical power losses. Proposed is an optimal control in normal mode power grids which considers the value of planned technical power losses. Improved method for determining normative values of technical energy losses using the criteria programming and neuro-fuzzy modeling is presented.'),
(3319, 1, 0, 9, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Faruk Ugranlı', 1, 'On the Importance of Renewable Data’s Spatial Dependence for Planning of Distribution Systems', 'Distribution network planning, wind power plant, solar power plant, random variable, spatial correlation', 'By the development of distribution network planning problems, random variables have become an important consideration as their correlation might be ignored for the simplicity. In this study, the impacts of spatial correlation in terms of distribution network planning problem are investigated by using a Monte Carlo Simulation based optimization framework. This model minimizes the investment and maintenance costs of substations, transformers, feeders, renewable generators while satisfying the chance constraints related to feeder capacities, voltage constraints, and substation capacities. In order to apply this model, an integer genetic algorithm is utilized along with the linearized load flow equations. The case studies applied through the modified 34-nodes test system show that the consideration of spatial correlation yields different investment results.'),
(3320, 1, 0, 11, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Tamara Ninković', 1, 'Coordination of electric vehicles charging in the distribution system', 'electric vehicles; coordinated optimal charging; power quality; uncoordinated charging; dual-tariff charging', 'As the environmental awareness has become crucial in 21st century, large penetration of electric vehicles (EVs) is expected in near future. However, integration of these vehicles in the existing distribution system will not be an easy task. Uncoordinated and random charging would cause problems such as overloads, voltage deviations and increased power losses. Thus, electric vehicle charging has to follow some optimal charging pattern that will reduce negative impact on the utility grid. This paper analyzes problems caused by EVs charging and proposes an optimal charging solution for coordinating charging of large number of electric vehicles. Therefore, three charging modes have been considered: uncoordinated, dual-tariff and coordinated charging. It is shown that the proposed coordinated charging solution has improved voltage profiles and reduced negative impact on the grid. All calculations are done in GAMS (General Algebraic Modeling System) environment, using CONOPT solver.'),
(3321, 1, 0, 11, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Vahid Helac', 1, 'Wind farm response on short circuits and longitudinal asymmetries', 'wind farm; short circuit; longitudinal asymmetries; renewables', 'The steady increase in electricity demand has led to more installed generation capacity in wind farms, which, due to the stochastic nature of their production, may have characteristic and non-standard responses to some occurrences in the grid. The power output from the wind farm changes constantly, depending on the wind speed, so the impact of the network on the wind farm will inversely vary depending on the moment of the short circuit and the wind farm operating mode, since the values of currents and voltages in these fault systems depend on the power flows. Although wind power is known to contribute to the short-circuit current / power at the point of its connection, this paper focuses on the response of the wind farm to short circuits in the network and the impact of these phenomena on the grid-wind relation. The aim of the paper is to determine the worst type of short circuit for wind turbine operation in the distribution system.'),
(3322, 0, 0, 8, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Jovan Mikulović', 1, 'Modeli za proračun difuznog zračenja na solarne kolektore', 'difuzna komponenta iradijanse; izotropski model; anizotropski model; solarni kolektor;', 'U radu su razmatrani najpoznatiji izotropski i anizotropski modeli za proračun difuzne komponente iradijanse na solarne kolektore. Dati su osnovni izrazi i istaknute su karakteristike pojedinih modela. Na osnovu mernih podataka o horizontalnoj iradijansi ispitane su mogućnosti primene pojedinih modela za proračun difuzne komponente iradijanse na solarne kolektore locirane na području Beograda.'),
(3323, 0, 0, 8, 'ENS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Kerim Obarcanin', 1, 'A High Voltage Circuit Breaker Behavior Change Indices based on the Vibration Signature Analysis', 'high voltage circuit breaker; vibration analysis, condition assessment, smart grid, fractal dimension', 'Fast, accurate and noninvasive methods for a High Voltage Circuit Breaker (HVCB) condition assessment are hot topics since the first breaker has been utilized in the electrical power grid. The HVCB is the key to the stable power system, so its fault diagnosis is of great significance.  The vibration signal obtained during the operation of the HVCB contains valuable information on its mechanical and structural integrity. Based on these premises, the paper present method for noninvasive HVCB condition assessment based on the vibration signature measurement. The proposed method is suitable for offline as well as online or monitoring based measurement systems. The core of the assessment method consists of variational mode decomposition and Higuchi fractal dimension estimation.'),
(3324, 1, 0, 12, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Drazen Brdjanin', 1, 'An Online Feasibility Calculator for Building the Photovoltaic Systems', 'feasibility calculator; online system; photovoltaic system; renewable energy source; solar power plant', 'The paper presents an online web-oriented system named SOLARS, which is aimed at calculating the feasibility of building the photovoltaic (PV) systems. SOLARS currently enables potential investors to calculate the technical and financial feasibility of building the PV systems in the Republic of Srpska (Bosnia and Herzegovina). Very intuitive GUI design enables investors to obtain feasibility calculations in three simple steps: (i) selection of a geographical location, (ii) specification of technical parameters, and (iii) specification of financial parameters. A usage scenario is illustrated by a real feasibility calculation example.'),
(3325, 0, 0, 24, 'ENS-1', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Optimization of electricity consumption in a compressor plant', 'compressed air; electricity energy ; control programs', 'As a result of monitoring and research in the industry, a proposal is made to save electricity in a complex compressor plant -  High pressure compressors, connected to five individual PET (polyethylene terephthalate) bottles.  Prior to production lines, they were connected to a single high-pressure tank.  In this way, the reliability of the system is increased.  The compressors are manufactured by AFcompressors and are under the pressure of 40 bar.   The driver is &quot;Airleader&quot;, which has multiple control modules.  We used the compressor station module.'),
(3326, 0, 0, 25, 'ENS-1', '2019', 1, 1, 'Karolina Kasaš-Lažetić', 1, 'Uticaj stubova mešovitog električnog voda na raspodelu magnetskog polja', 'armirano betonski stub; čelično rešetkasti stub; magnetsko polje; mešovit vod; elektromagnetska indukcija', 'U radu je izvršena uporedna analiza magnetskog polja u okolini mešovitog trofaznog nadzemnog voda, postavljenog na čelično rešetkaste i armirano betonske stubove. U proračunima je uzet u obzir uticaj promene faznog stava jačina struja, kako u srednjenaponskom, tako i u niskonaponskom sistemu mešovitog voda. Akcenat je stavljen na ispitivanje uticaja na raspodelu magnetskog polja struja indukovanih u feromagnetskim, provodnim delovima stubova. Proračun je izvršen numerički, koristeći programski paket Comsol Multiphysics, koji se bazira na primeni metoda konačnih elemenata, na dvodimenzionalnom modelu mešovitog voda. Rezultati ukazuju na to da se usled indukovanih struja u feromagnetskim provodnim delovima stubova intenzitet vektora magnetske indukcije smanjio u oblasti oko stubova. Pojava je izrazitija kod čelično rešetkastih stubova, a nešto manje izrazita kod armirano betonskih stubova.'),
(3327, 0, 0, 9, 'ENS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Levon Gevorkov', 1, 'Simulation Model for Efficiency Estimation of Photovoltaic Water Pumping System', 'pumps, water pumps, matlab, energy efficiency, photovoltaic systems, simulation', 'The simulation model for efficiency estimation of\r\nthe solar water pumping system is proposed. It investigates the\r\npossibility of efficiency calculation for the designed Centrifugal\r\nPump System (CPS) with a Photovoltaic (PV) power source. The\r\nefficiency of the CPS varies significantly with the change of\r\noperational point location on the H-Q plane and depends on the\r\npositions of the pump and system curves. The model allows not\r\nonly to estimate efficiency for a given PV water pumping system\r\nbut also to implement it later at the design stage of a real PV\r\npumping system for preliminary performance analysis. Modelbased calculation approach for the single-drive centrifugal pump\r\nalong with other necessary parts is described. All parameters of\r\nthe current simulation model can be varied according to the\r\nneeds of the desired configuration. The model helps to estimate\r\nand optimize the system parameters of the PV water pumping\r\nsystem in the wide range of consumption demand.'),
(3328, 0, 0, 2, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Sani Šarčević', 1, 'Sistem za distribuciju vremena i frekvencije putem fiber optičkih linkova korištenjem WR-PTP protokola, Demonstracija mogućnosti i evaluacija performansi', '14', 'Pouzdan referentni izvor vremena i frekvencije je ključan za ispravno funkcionisanje velikih telekomunikacionih i elektroenergetskih sistema. Većina njih se oslanja na navigacijske satelitske sisteme, koji ne nude garanciju pružanja usluge niti osiguranja kvaliteta, a satelitske signale je relativno jednostavno ometati ili lažirati. Ovaj članak demonstrira mogućnost distribucije sljedivog signala vremena i frekvencije iz Instituta za mjeriteljstvo BiH do krajnjih korisnika putem komercijalne fiber optičke infrastrukture. Najprije je ukratko predstavljena međunarodna vremenska skala i njena realizacija u BiH, te konvencionalni sistemi za distribuciju. Zatim je opisan predloženi sistem, elementi i princip rada. Realizovan je link dužine 5 km te su evaluirane performanse. Postignuta je tačnost distribucije vremena reda 100 ps u odnosu na referentni signal i stabilnosti frekvencije reda 1e-11 na intervalu 1s.'),
(3329, 1, 0, 1, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nemanja Radosavljević', 1, 'Pregled sigurnosnih pretnji i mehanizama prevencije i zaštite u bežičnim senzorskim mrežama s primenom u preciznoj poljoprivredi', 'Bežične senzorske mreže; precizna poljoprivreda; bezbednost podataka; detekcija napada; mehanizmi zaštite', 'U radu su prikazani aktuelni problemi bezbednosti prenosa podataka sa aspekta precizne poljoprivrede i ograničavajući faktori koje sa sobom donosi tehnologija bežičnih senzorskih mreža. Da bi se ovi problemi rešili ili predupredili, detaljno smo predstavili različite tipove napada u bežičnim senzorskim mrežama, kao i mehanizme detekcije, prevencije i odbrane od pomenutih napada.'),
(3330, 0, 0, 3, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Irena Seremet', 1, 'Advancing Multiprotocol Label Switching Traffic Engineering with Segment Routing in Software Defined Network environment', 'MPLS, Traffic-Engineering, Segment Routing, SDN, PCEP', 'Multiprotocol Label Switching Traffic-Engineering (MPLS TE) is a mechanism for optimizing network performances by using existing routing and resource reservation protocols in order to calculate and establish tunnels used for transporting different traffic flows depending on their destination. Aim of this paper is to present benefits of using Segment Routing Traffic Engineering (SR-TE) in Software Defined Network (SDN) environment in order to overcome several MPLS TE problems and challenges presented in this paper. In order to present benefits of SR-TE in SDN, two scenarios are compared. In first scenario SR is implemented in classical IP/MPLS network. In the second scenario, SDN controller is added to a topology and control over paths is delegated to SDN controller.'),
(3331, 0, 0, 4, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Irena Seremet', 1, 'Advances of configuring Quality of Service (QoS) in Software Defined Networks (SDN) by using meter table', 'IP, Mininet, Quality of Service, Software Defined Networks', 'New technologies introduce more services which will call for significant advances and changes in IP networks. Networks will have to go in the direction of network programmability, virtualization and cloud-based services. In this paper, Quality of Service (QoS) is configured in two different environments: (i) in traditional IP network using QoS policy-maps and (i) in Software Defined Network. Two scenarios are compared in order to emphasize the benefits of using SDN technology when providing QoS provisioning mechanisms.'),
(3332, 0, 0, 5, 'KST', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'An algorithm for applying DFT in digital signal filtering and implementation in Matlab', 'Digital signal analysis; Fourier transform (FT) and DFT, filtering algorithms; implementation in Matlab software.', 'Discrete signals and systems are represented in the frequency range by Fourier transform (FT).  Fourier transform is a continuous function and as such is not suitable for processing on a computer.  The discrete Fourier transform (DFT) is generated by discretizing one period of the Fourier transform.  With DFT, it is possible to transform N-Fir filters, each of which is implemented as a demodulator and then an NF filter..  The importance of FT in signal processing is large.  The most important application is spectral signal analysis and frequency domain filtering.  This paper will show the application of DFT to filter different types of signals and implementations through coding and simulation in Matlab.  The implementation of digital filters and their implementation through computers can be hardware and software depending on the algorithm for designing a digital signal filter.  In this paper, basic algorithmic solutions for software implementation of IIR and FIR digital filters implementation structure are presented.'),
(3333, 0, 0, 6, 'KST', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Example of Cloud Speech API usage and interpretation of recognized content on the E-ink display', 'Cloud Speech API, E-ink display, communication', 'Virtual communication has become a frequent activity in XXI century. This form of communication is used online, via voice or SMS messages. Accelerated lifestyle and increasing technological development require a faster way of establishing communication between two people. This paper presents one of the custom types of accelerated communication. Using the Cloud Speech API, speech recognition and conversion to text format are performed. Identified content from an Android device which communicates with a public server is transferred to an Arduino UNO to which an E-ink display is connected, to show the received content.\r\nUsing this system accelerates communication with people who are unable to communicate in another way, while maintaining privacy.\r\nBenefits of use are portability and small dimensions, which make the content easy to view without using a mobile device.'),
(3334, 0, 0, 5, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Tamara Skoric', 1, 'The reduction of artifacts in the EKG signal recorded while driving the car', '113', 'The paper proposes a new method for eliminating specific artifacts that occur in electrocardiogram (ECG) signals while driving. The signals are recorded capacitive electrodes placed in the car seat. The method is based on the estimation of the fluctuation of the signal segments after the elimination of the trend. The Detrended Fluctuation Analysis (DFA), originally designed to determine the statistical self-affinity, was used. The proposed method was verified using ECG signals with correct parts manually annotated by two medical experts.'),
(3335, 0, 0, 10, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Aleksandar Lebl', 1, 'Combined Jamming in RCIED Activation Prevention', 'RCIED; combined jamming; simulation program; BER; phasor diagram', 'The characteristics of combined sweep and barrage jamming of RCIED activation messages comparing to pure sweep and pure barrage jamming are presented in this paper. It is proved when combined jamming is advantageous over other two other jamming methods as also when it gives no benefits. The activation and jamming signal characteristics when combined jamming is especially effective are emphasized in the paper. The combined jamming performances are determined on the base of originally developed and verified simulation program.'),
(3336, 0, 0, 9, 'KST', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Evaluation of Nonlinear Distortion on Use  of mmWave 5G Waveforms', '5G, FBMC; UFMC; GFDM; Spectral Efficiency.', 'Different multi-carrier waveforms are being investigated as prospective candidates for the 5G radio interface. In this paper, we evaluate the waveform of two leading 5G waveform candidates such as Filter Bank Multi-Carrier (FBMC) and Universal Filtered Multi-Carrier (UFMC) for Sub-6 GHz and mmWave 5G wireless transmitters. Simulated output power spectra of the power amplifier (PA) for 5G FBMC 5 MHz waveform and different input power levels are presented. Experimental output power spectra of the power amplifier for 3 MHz 5G UFMC and FBMC signals and input power of -10 dBm at 0.70 GHz are illustrated. In this case, the nonlinear distortion of about 20 dBc is achieved.'),
(3337, 0, 0, 6, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Tatjana Kapus', 1, 'Improving Success of Sending From Two Mutually Hidden 802.15.4 Nodes', 'access protocols; formal specifications; performance evaluation; personal area networks', 'This paper presents an interesting result obtained for IEEE 802.15.4 nonbeacon-enabled wireless personal area networks. We consider a network in which two mutually hidden nodes send one data frame to the central node. By using the statistical model-checking capability of the PRISM model checker, we have analysed the probability that the central node successfully receives the data frame of both nodes. For larger data frame sizes, this probability is equal to zero. We show that an additional node within the range of both mutually hidden nodes which transmits one data frame like the latter considerably improves this probability both in the case of using the medium access control protocol with acknowledgements and without them.'),
(3338, 1, 0, 2, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Darko Šuka', 1, 'An overview of EMF exposure assessment metrics', 'RF sources, EMF exposure, Exposure metrics, Exposure quantities, Incident field, Power density', 'With the arrival of new, more powerful radio-frequency (RF) energy sources, the potential risks associated with human exposure to electromagnetic fields (EMF) also increased. This brought the necessity of developing appropriate security regulations, as well as standardized measurement and exposure evaluation techniques. This paper gives a brief overview of current metrics used for the assessment of exposure to RF-EMFs.');
INSERT INTO `rad` (`id`, `poster`, `virtual`, `rb`, `sesija`, `simpozijum`, `prihvacen`, `prezentovan`, `prezentovao`, `objavljen`, `naslov`, `k_rijeci`, `sazetak`) VALUES
(3339, 1, 0, 3, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Darko Šuka', 1, 'Comparative analysis of E field strength via software simulations and measurements for GSM/DCS/UMTS downlink frequency bands', 'EM waves, EM simulation, Propagation prediction, Power density distribution, Base station', 'This paper discusses the software simulations of RF     electromagnetic fields (EMFs) distribution for an outdoor scenario in a densely populated urban area, the practical realization of simulations and the comparative analysis of simulation and measurement results. The goal was to predict the EMF strength with a slightly different approach in relation to the mobile operators who are focused on the planning of area coverage to support the voice and data traffic at a level of quality expected by the users. In this regard, Wireless InSite® software has been used to estimate the maximum values of the EMF total power density distribution and Erms strengths caused by the radiation of all base stations in the observed area.'),
(3340, 0, 1, 13, 'VRT', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Zaštita od udara groma i prenapona objekta Telekoma - praktično iskustvo', 'mini link; prenapon; udar groma; Interceptor SI 25; uzemljenje; Ericore kabal; odvodnik prenapona; antenski stub; klasa odvodnika; LPMS ( Lightning Electromagnetic Impuls); varničar; varistor; nivo zaštite; LPA 04.', 'Predmet rada je zaštita mini linka zajedno sa antenom na stubu i objekta Telekoma od direktnog, odnosno indirektnog  udara groma i prenapona, odnosno negativnih posledica pojave istih. Do prenapona u kabelskim instalacijama kao i u elektri-čnim i elektronskim uređajima uglavnom dolazi zbog indukcije u slučaju direktnog udara groma u objekat ili u njegovu blizinu, odnosno preklopnih manipulacija ili kvarova u energetskom si-stemu napajanja.'),
(3341, 1, 0, 4, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Vladimir Maksimović', 1, 'Analiza bitskog protoka transpondera za satelitsku televiziju', 'DVB-S; DVB-S2; satelitska televizija; MPEG-2; MPEG-4; HEVC; HDTV; SDTV', 'U ovom radu je urađena analiza bitskog protoka transpondera za satelitsku televiziju. Analiza je urađena za satelit Eutelsat 16A koji se nalazi na poziciji 16°E (istočno) pomoću uređaja DiviCatch i softverskog paketa DiviSuite. Sa ovog satelita se emituje više od 80% TV kanala namenjenih zemljama Zapadnog Balkana. Tabelarno je dat pregled transpondera, tehnički parametri i broj SDTV i HDTV kanala. Grafički su predstavljeni dobijeni rezultati za prosečne vrednosti bitskog protoka i pojedinačni bitski protoci svakog TV kanala. Rezultati pokazuju da se najveći broj SDTV i HDTV kanala emituje u DVB-S2 standardu koristeći MPEG-4 kompresiju i 8PSK modulacionu tehiku. Analiza pokazuje da provajderi prilikom prenosa HDTV kanala čak 28% koriste manji bitski protok od propisanog minimuma, dok je za SDTV kanale to 2%.'),
(3342, 0, 0, 7, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Ejmel Terzi', 1, 'A Game Theoretic Study for Distributed Multiprotocol Coexistence in ISM Band', 'MIMO; coexistence in ISM band; game theory', 'Developing internet of things (IoT) applications have led to an interest in coexistence between IEEE 802.11 and IEEE 802.15.4 standards. Moreover, existence and efficiency of steady state point for those scenarios are the critical issues because of asynchronous bandwidth and power properties of these standards. In this article, we present a noncooperative game model in which 802.11 links can select the optimal transmit/receive beamformer pair with the release of 802.11n standard while 802.15.4 devices only update the output power of single antenna. The regret matching learning algorithm running at 802.11n receivers achieves an equilibrium point in noncooperative fashion. The results show that the coarse correlated equilibrium exists, and the total power consumed in equilibrium is the near optimal solution.'),
(3343, 1, 0, 5, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nenad Petrović', 1, 'Software environment for performance of relay signal by DF technique influenced by k-µ fading', '1: Probability density function (PDF), 2: Cumulative distribution function (CDF), 3: Outage probability (Pout), 4: Smart city, 5: Quality of Service.', 'This paper considers the transmission of signals under the influence of k-µ fading, which model a random process of changing the amplitude of a useful signal using a relay system using the Decode-and-Forward (DF) technique. Since the interference is significant in today‘s wireless networks, the channel model ignores influence of receiver noise on the system performance. Contribution of the paper is derived infinite-series expression observing important wireless performance criteria for outage probability (Pout). In the proposed system, the transmission time has been divided into two phases to be used by the decode and forward protocol. The first phase has been allocated for the source to transmit its data whereas the relays and destination nodes are in receiving mode. In addition, the paper presents a tool to illustrate the proposed approach, which allows modeling and simulating scenarios of web cities.'),
(3344, 1, 0, 6, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Vladimir Maksimović', 1, 'Struktura TV kanala satelitskih operatera i DTH platformi u Evropi', 'satelitski operater; DTH; SDTV; HDTV; UHDTV', 'U ovom radu je predstavljena struktura TV kanala koji se distribuiraju sa satelitskih pozicija sa kojih DTH platforme pružaju usluge u zemljama Evrope. Struktura je razmatrana u pogledu: dostupnost servisa (FTA i PAY TV), rezolucije (SDTV, HDTV i UHDTV), standarda za emitovanje (DVB-S i DVB-S2), satelitskih operatera i satelitskih pozicija. Prikupljeni podaci su predstavljeni tabelarno i grafički za period od 1996. do 2019. godine.'),
(3345, 0, 0, 11, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Damir Zaborski', 1, 'Primena korporativnih bežičnih TCP/IP mreža na železnici', 'Ključne reči 1; bežična mreža, 2; pristupna tačka 3; železnica', 'Pored zapaženog razvoja mobilnih mreža (trenutno je u toku standardizacija 5G sistema), u svetu je prisutan i intenzivan razvoj drugih tipova bežičnih mreža, posebno računarskih, koje omogućavaju velike brzine prenosa. Aktuelna je i primena bežičnih senzorskih mreža i Internet of Things (IoT) koncepta umrežavanja.\r\nRazvoj novih mrežnih radio tehnologija zasniva se na konceptu pristupa bežičnim uređajima na bazi instaliranja malih ćelija ili pristupnih tačaka, koje su povezane u grupe brzim optičkim mrežama. Tako se ostvaruje saradnja unutar grupe da bi se zajednički upravljalo resursima u datoj mrežnoj oblasti.\r\nStvaranje pametnih transportnih sistema prilagođenih okolini i mobilnosti je među visokim prioritetima u razvoju saobraćaja širom sveta. Železnički prevoz je prepoznat kao vitalni deo ovog procesa. \r\nU radu su prikazane mogućnosti bežičnih pristupnih tehnologija, dat je opšti predlog arhitekture i implementacije bežičnih pristupnih mreža na železnici.'),
(3346, 0, 0, 1, 'KST', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Mid-Infrared Suspended Silicon and Germanium Photonics for Sensing Applications', 'silicon photonics, mid-infrared, sensors', 'The mid-infrared (MIR) wavelength region (3-15 micrometers) contains unique absorption fingerprints of many molecules and substances. Therefore, the main application area in the MIR can be sensing. Silicon and Germanium are transparent in this range (Si up to 8 um, and Ge up to 15 um) and due to their excellent electrical and optical properties and CMOS compatibility they can offer suitable platforms for the realisation of compact MIR sensors. However, claddings used for the telecom wavelength range are usually not suitable at longer wavelengths due to high absorption, so alternative solutions need to be investigated. In this paper we present our recent results on suspended Si and Ge devices (waveguides, couplers and detectors) that can exploit full transparency ranges of Si and Ge.'),
(3347, 0, 0, 4, 'KST', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'EFFECTS OF 5G MOBILE PHONE RADIATION ON HUMAN ORGANISM', 'mobile phone; radio waves; radiation, electromagnetic field strength; specific absorption rate; base station.', 'This paper points out the effects of 5G mobile phone radiation on a human organism. The existing standards are based on electromagnetic field thermal effects on a human organism. In this paper the permissible values from the standards have been compared with the calculation results concerning field intensity, measured field values and experimental data from literature. This served as a base for the determination of the antenna safety distance. Besides the thermal effect, there is interference as well as homeopathic effect whose influence has not been investigated yet. Some advice on using mobile phones are given in order to reduce harmful radiation.'),
(3348, 1, 0, 7, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Zoran Milivojević', 1, 'Razumljivost govora u ambijentu ranih refleksija Gausovog i difuznog šuma', 'Razumljivost; Refleksije, Difuzioni šum; STOI; SMST baza.', 'U prvom delu rada analiziran je efekat razumljivosti u prisustvu ambijentalnih smetnji (refleksija, Gausov šum i šum ambijenta). U drugom delu rada opisan je eksperiment u kome je testirana razumljivost govora kod izgovaranja rečenica na srpskom jeziku u prisustvu snažne prve refleksije, Gausovog šuma i šuma ambijenta. Rezultati eksperimenta su prikazani tabelarno i grafički. Na kraju je izvršena komparativna analiza razumljivosti i izvršena klasifikacija razumljivosti u odnosu na standard IEC 60268-16: 2011.'),
(3349, 1, 0, 22, 'P-3', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Otpornost Schur watermarking algoritma kod IS mapiranja na filtriranje audio signala Notch filtrom', 'Schur dekompozicija; watermarking, Notch filtar', 'U ovom radu izvršena je analiza robusnosti SD watermarking algoritma kod IS mapiranja na filtriranje audio signala Notch filtrom. U prvom delu rada opisan je SD algoritam za insertovanje i ekstrakciju vodenog žiga u sliku. Nakon toga dat je prikaz konverzije slike sa insertovanim žigom u audio signal i Notch filtar. U drugom delu rada prikazan je eksperiment u okviru koga je vršeno testiranje robusnosti Schur algoritma u odnosu na filtriranje Notch filtrom. Notch filtar je realizovan sa širinom-r i centrom- θ nepropusnog osega. Dobijeni rezultati analizirani su primenom objektivnih (MSE i NC) i subjektivnih (vizuelni kvalitet) mera kvaliteta.'),
(3350, 1, 0, 8, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Zeljko Ivanovic', 1, 'Characterization of LoRaWAN Wireless Sensors Network in Outdoor and Indoor Conditions', 'LoRaWAN; wireless sensor network; outdoor and indoor testing; gateway; end node', 'In this paper the results of an experimental testing of a LoRaWAN wireless sensor network in the open area of Banja Luka city are presented. Also, testing of LoRaWAN network was done within one business facility. The results obtained are presented graphically. Based on these results, the drawn conclusions may assist in the planning and establishment of the LoRaWAN network both indoors and outdoors.'),
(3351, 1, 0, 9, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nikola Vasić', 1, 'Statistics of simultaneous Rice, Nakagami-m and α-µ fadings after SC combining', 'fading;diversity reception;signal combinig; statistical signal description', 'This paper presents initial results of a research towards statistical description of diversity-combined wireless signals that propagate over different environments. This kind of situation is encountered when receiver has multiple input antennas which are positioned in such a way that the fading environment cannot be considered uniform for all propagating paths of signals. We consider a three-input SC combiner with three different fading statistics on each of them, and derive the probability density function and cumulative distribution for the output signal. The results can be further used for calculating various system performance measures.'),
(3352, 0, 0, 5, 'KST', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'An Evaluation of 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz ISM Radio Bands Utilization in Backhaul IP Microwave Wireless Networks', 'Industrial Scientific and Medical (ISM) radio bands, 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz, IP Microwave Backhaul, Time Division Multiple Access (TDMA), Time Division Duplex (TDD), IP Microwave Wireless Communication Technology, Spectrum Efficiency, Wireless Customer Premises Equipment (WCPE), Point to Point (PtP), Point to Multi Point (PtMP).', 'In preceding few decades there have been an exceptional   development and progress in the area of backhaul IP Microwave Wireless communication technology. One of the causes of this rapid growth is the use of Industrial Scientific and Medical (ISM) radio bands often known as free bands for radio transmission and reception. IP Microwave radio links operates in 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz Industrial Scientific and Medical (ISM) radio bands. For minimizing operational and capital cost IP Microwave radio links operating in 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz Industrial Scientific and Medical (ISM) radio bands are the most viable communication technologies of recent times. As in ISM radio bands operators do not have to purchase a designated frequency channel for radio transmission and reception. This results in cost saving and spectrum efficiency across the globe as the Microwave band is mostly populated in metropolitan cities around the world. In the first section of this research work authors have evaluated the pros and cons of the 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz Industrial Scientific and Medical (ISM) radio bands and in second section authors have recommended the use of 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz Industrial Scientific and Medical (ISM) radio bands depending upon the deployment scenarios and area of interest according to user define applications and minimum bandwidth required for the transmission and reception of delay and jitter free stream of Multimedia traffic.'),
(3353, 1, 0, 1, 'P-3', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Monitoring of Pasture in Rotational Grazing', 'Pasture; Grazing; Mapping', 'Continues reduction of people working in agriculture has led to an increase of implementation of automation in this domain. In animal breeding and feeding the lack of people is drastic. In order to minimize losses due to lack of people, different methods for monitoring of pasture in rotational grazing will be analyzed. This paper will analyze possibilities of implementation of a robotic system that will enable: analysis of pastures in the animal pursuit of grazing, identification of the space that is optimal for grazing at that moment, and defining GPS coordinates that will determine the limits of cattle keeping, during rotational grazing.'),
(3354, 0, 0, 2, 'PRS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Aleksandra Koprivica', 1, 'Uticaj tehnologije 3D štampe na dimenzionu tačnost proizvoda', 'dimenziona tačnost; 3D štampa', 'Danas se složeni trodimenzionalni objekati često  proizvode procesima 3D štampanja iz računarskih dizajna (CAD modela), obično uzastopnim dodavanjem materijala sloj po sloj, zbog čega se nazivaju i aditivnom proizvodnjom. Zbog svojih brojnih prednosti, kao što su: ekonomičnija proizvodnja dimenzionalno prihvatljivih oblika, te relativno velika brzina štampe, uglavnom su u upotrebi 3D printeri koji kao osnovnu komponentu koriste plastičnu nit, koja se topi i istiskuje kroz metalnu diznu, te lijepi za podlogu ili prethodni sloj, prema komandama G koda, koje dobija iz odgovarajučeg softvera. Debljina sloja se kreće od 0,15 mm do 0,2 mm, a površina koja se formira ima jasno slojevitu strukturu. U radu je prikazana uporedna analiza dimenzione tačnosti objekta izrađenog inkjet postupkom - 3D printerom koji za materijal koristi plastiku, u odnosu na objekat štampan iz prahа i vezivnog sredstva FDM postupkom, za različite debljine slojeva.'),
(3355, 0, 0, 3, 'PRS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Srđan Damjanović', 1, 'Međunarodna interkomparacija mjerenja izvršenih sa digitalnog multimetra HP3458A', 'međupoređenje; napon; struja; otpor; mjerna nesigurnost;', 'U radu je predstavljeno međunarodno međulaboratorijsko poređenje mjerenja DC napona u devet mjernih tačaka, AC napona u devet mjernih tačaka, DC struje u šest mjernih tačaka, AC struje u četiri mjerne tačke i otpora u šest mjernih tačaka sa digitalnim multimetrom HP3458A, koji je korišćen kao putujući etalon. Pilot laboratorija i organizator ovog međulaboratorijskog poređenja bila je VSL B.V. laboratorija iz Holandije. U ovom međulaboratorijskom poređenju učestvovalo je 28 laboratorija iz Belgije, Bosne i Hercegovine, Francuske, Njemačke,  Italije, Litvanije, Luksemburga, Holandije, Norveške, Portugala, Švedske, i Švajcarske. \r\nMetrološka laboratorija Orao a.d. Bijeljina bila je jedina metrološka laboratorija iz Bosne i Hercegovine, koja je učestvovala u ovom međulaboratorijskom poređenju.  Kao etalon za generisanje DC napona, AC napona, DC struje, AC struje i otpora korišćen je univerzalni kalibrator Fluke 5520, a za mjerenje smo koristili naš digitalni multimetar HP3458A. Da bi se olakšalo očitavanje i zapisivanje mjernih rezultata direktno na računar, napravljen je program u programskom jeziku VEEPro za automatsko mjerenje sa digitalnim multimetrom HP3458A. Metrološka laboratorija Orao a.d. Bijeljina je za sve mjerne tačke u ovom međunarodnom međulaboratorijskom poređenju potvrdila svoje mjerne metode i proračune mjerne nesigurnosti za etaloniranje mjerača DC napona, AC napona, DC struje, AC struje i otpora.'),
(3356, 0, 0, 4, 'PRS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Dragan Rodić', 1, 'Application of ANFIS for modeling and predicting the EDM surface roughness', 'electrical discharge machining; neuro-fuzzy system; machining quality', 'Machining quality is very important performance characteristics of electrical discharge machining (EDM). This paper presents the development and application of an adaptive neuro-fuzzy inference system (ANFIS) in the EDM process for prediction of quality parameters. In this ANFIS architecture, discharge current and pulse duration are input variables and output variable is surface roughness. The proposed ANFIS approach in this study provides a more precise selection of the input parameters in electrical discharge machining, which leads to better productivity and product quality.'),
(3357, 0, 0, 5, 'PRS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Saša Tešić', 1, 'Application of Taguchi method for identifying optimum specific energy consumption in CNC face milling', 'specific energy consumption, Taguchi method, optimization', 'In the present study, the effect and optimization of three cutting parameters, namely depth of cut, cutting speed and feed rate on the specific energy consumption in the face milling was investigated by using the Taguchi method. Experiments were carried out in wet condition as per Taguchi’s L9 orthogonal array. The cutting parameters were optimized using signal-to-noise ratio, whereas analysis of variance was employed to determine the significance of the process parameters influencing the specific energy consumption. The results revealed that feed rate and depth of cut are the most significant parameters affecting specific energy consumption. The confirmation test is conducted at optimum cutting conditions and it is found that the Taguchi method was notably successful in the optimization.'),
(3358, 0, 0, 6, 'PRS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Vladimir Blanuša', 1, 'Analiza uticaja strategije 3D štampe na vreme štampe primenom "ZORTRAX M200 plus" štampača', '3D štampa; „Z-SUITE“ softver; strategije formiranja oblika, vreme izrade modela', 'U radu je izvršena analiza uticaja predloženih strategija formiranja oblika 3D štampom na proizvodnost primenom metode FDM (Fuzed deposition modeling). Za potrebe analize korišćen je štampač "ZORTRAX M200 plus" sa softverom Z-suite. Navedena metoda i dostupna oprema brze izrade prototipa omogućuju formiranje prototipa rastapanjem različitih materijala temperature topljenja do 300°C i njegovim nanošenjem u slojevima. Takođe, u radu je izvršeno poređenje mase dobijenog prototipa u zavisnosti od primenjene strategije formiranja oblika za konkretan primer.'),
(3359, 0, 0, 7, 'PRS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Aleksandar Košarac', 1, 'Cutting parameters influence on surface roughness in Al 7075 milling', 'component;  End milling, surface roughness, design of experiment, orthogonal array, Taguchi method, analysis of variance', 'Aluminum and its alloys are nowadays a very commonly used material in the aerospace and automotive industries. Due to its good mechanical properties, low density, high hardness, good thermal properties, and good machinability, Al7075 is one of the most commonly used aluminum alloys.  This work investigates the effect of cutting parameters on surface roughness in  finish milling of Al7075 aluminum alloy. Considering the negative effects of conventional cutting fluids (coolants and lubricants), oils or water emulsions on the environment and health, and the negative economic effects resulting from the foregoing, this study also analyzes the possibilities the use of different coolant-lubricant types on cutting. In this connection, the subject of research is also the influence of the cooling method on surface roughness in end milling.'),
(3360, 0, 0, 8, 'PRS', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Resekciona tumorska endoproteza „Spacer”', 'tumorska endoproteza; CAD/CAE/CAM tehnologije', 'Jedna od metoda koje omogućuju saniranje malignih oboljenja medijalnog dela dugih kostiju, nadlaktice, podkolenice i butne kosti predstavlja hirurško odstranjivanje obolelog koštanog i okolnog mekog tkiva i ugradnja specijalne custom - made tumorske endoproteze „Spacer”. Projektovanje i izrada tumorske endoproteze „Spacer” predstavlja kompleksnu proceduru koja započinje obradom dijagnostičkih snimaka Rtg ili MRI. Na osnovu ovako dobijenih snimaka mogu se dovoljno pouzdano odrediti geometrijski parametri obolele kosti koja se snima kao i dopunski podaci neophodni za razvoj endoproteze.  Na osnovu geometrijskih parametra omogućeno je definisanje računarskog modela kosti a na osnovu nje i tumorske endoproeteze „Spacer”. Na taj način se moguća je simulacija ugradnje, koa i simulacija biomehaničkog opterećenja i uklještenja. Primenom metode konačnih elemenata definiše se stanje napona i stanje deformacija kao i položaj maksimalnih Von Misseovih napona. Na kraju se primenom CAM tehnologije izrađuje endoprotezu „Spacer” spremna za ugradnju.'),
(3361, 0, 0, 10, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mihajlo Travar', 1, 'Sajber bezbjednost u Republici Srpskoj/Bosni i Hercegovini sa naglaskom na energetski sektor', 'Cyber security, energy sector, Information and Communications Technologies, network', 'Cyber Space has become an important component of society, considering that institutions, energy and financial sector, school system and social life in general depend of internet and interconnectedeness. On a teritory of Republic of Srpska/ Bosnia and Herzegovina significant place takes energy sector, so its security is a basis of this countrys functioning. Energy sector and sector of information and communication technologies are two technological branches that act synergistically on the development of the whole society. Deviations from the proper functioning of information systems or parts in the energy sector not only present technical difficulties, but a much greater security hazard. Considering the trends of increasing cyber attacks on energy systems, it is important to consider security aspects of the integration of IKT tecnologies, as well as predict tools, proceedures, technologies and human resources so that energy systems can overcome security challenges ahead.'),
(3362, 1, 0, 7, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 1, 'Jovan Šetrajčić', 1, 'ANALYSIS OF CONFINEMENT EFFECTS ON THE FUNDAMENTAL CHARACTERISTICS OF PHONON NANOFILMS DEVELOPED BY SOFTWARE PACKAGE JoigS', 'Software package, phonons, spectra and states, ultra-thin film, confinement effects', 'JoigS is a computational package for calculating and expounding phonon system properties. It is based on the theory of perturbations in solid state physics using Green\'s functions and methodology of difference equation calculus. It must be used within Wolfram Mathematica and with the support of adequate graphic editing software. The package is easy to use to determine the basic (micro) properties of phonons, but with the ability to extend to the calculation of thermodynamic (macro) properties of a wide range of materials ranging from massive (balk) to nanoscopic structures. Here we present a calculation and graphical representation of the energy spectra and spatial distribution of phonon states in ultrathin crystalline films with different boundary conditions.'),
(3363, 0, 0, 3, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Prithvi Bhattacharya', 1, 'Safeguarding Intelligent Decision-Making for Business : Towards A Model', 'Cyber Security, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Decision Making', 'The growing use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in the business world and its effects continue to dominate debates given their penetration in the organizational processes including business decision-making. This article scrutinizes the application of AI technologies in the organizational processes and the security inferences for such establishments with a particular focus on\r\ndecision-making processes within the business context. The importance of this study is that it provides a new procedural design that deliberates the safety implications of organizational decision-making aided by the AI systems. The analysis is based on a combination of literature on organization decision making and AI technology security concerns. Additionally, this mirrors the need to empirically test this novel model using different case studies.'),
(3364, 0, 0, 4, 'RSS-1', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Maritime Single Window i mogucnost unapredjenja luckog poslovanja', 'MSW, FAL Konvencija,jedinstveni prozori, WTMIS', 'Svrha jedinstvenog prozora u pomorstvu (MSW-Maritime Single Window, engl.) je digitalizacija i pojednostavljenje administrativnih procedura prije uplovljenja/isplovljenja broda u/iz luku/e, u skladu sa zahtjevima EU Direktive 2010/65 o formalnostima pri izvještavanju (Reporting Formalities Directive, engl.). \r\nMSW ima za cilj pojednostavljenje i harmonizaciju administrativnih procedura u pomorstvu, standardizovanjem elektronske razmjene informacija i racionalizacijom formalnosti pri uplovljenju/isplovljenja broda u/iz luku/e. Administrativne procedure se unificiraju kroz tzv. FAL 1-7 forme koje su u skladu sa FAL Konvencijom (Convention on Facilitation of International Maritime Traffic, engl.). Ova Konvencija uključuje i dodatne informacije i/ili dokumenta koje treba dostaviti, ili koje organi vlasti mogu da traže, prilikom uplovljenja/isplovljenja broda u/iz luku/e.\r\nInfo-komunikacioni sistem ovog tipa je prvi put implementiran u Velikoj Britaniji, ali funkcioniše nezavisno od EU SafetyNet mreže. Ovdje je interesantno primijetiti da je sistem na taj način bio tehnički spreman za Brexit koji je uslijedio kasnije. \r\nU okvirima EU, šest zemalja članica radi na prototipovima nacionalnih jedinstvenih prozora u pomorstvu (National Maritime Single window, engl.) i to: Bugarska, Grčka, Italija, Malta, Rumunija i Norveška.'),
(3365, 0, 0, 1, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'George Papageorgiou', 1, 'Exploring the Prospects of Developing a Smartphone Application for Pedestrians', 'Software Development, Smartphone App, Information and Communication Technology (ICT), Survey Method, Sustainable Mobility, Pedestrian Navigation, Smart Pedestrian Network (SPN)', 'This paper explores the prospects for developing a smartphone application to promote walking and sustainable mobility. The investigation is based on a review of available Information and Communication Technology (ICT) as well as existing applications. A survey is also carried out in order to evaluate young peoples’ attitudes on aspects of active mobility and the necessity for a smart pedestrian application. The collected data was statistically analyzed, whereby important requirements were elicited for software development. It was shown that the survey method is an effective way for gathering initial requirements and verifying whether it is worthwhile to proceed to software development and implementation. Regarding the application, young people are quite positive on the prospects for a smart pedestrian navigation system.'),
(3366, 0, 1, 6, 'VRT', '2020', 1, 1, 'Srećko Stamenković', 1, 'A VISUAL AND INTERACTIVE TOOL FOR LEARNING FINITE AUTOMATA', 'automata theory, finite automata, simulation system, computer science education', 'Simulation tools for computer-assisted learning are widespread at all levels of education. They are recognized as tools for the effective study of complex and abstract systems. Traditional learning of automata theory is not easy for students to visualize theoretical constructs, so in this case, simulation systems are a great blend of theoretical and practical experience. This paper presents a tool developed with the aim of simplifying and visually presenting abstract concepts and mathematical models of automata theory to students. Constructing finite automata is possible in a graph editor in the form of a state diagram or by defining a transition function using a transition table. The simulator allows converting regular expressions to DFA or NFA, as well as simulating the Thompson algorithm.'),
(3367, 0, 0, 7, 'RSS-1', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'APPLICATION OF SIMILAR-TASK ALGORITHM TO COMPARE PERFORMANCE BETWEEN GRAPH AND RELATIONAL DATABASE', 'Relational data base, Graph data base, Similar-Task algoritam, SQL, NoSQL', 'Relational databases are currently the most needed concept for storing data, and they represent an organized collection of data in which data is organized into a set of relationships. With the development of a large number of applications, a huge amount of data has been created, where relational databases have proven to be less adequate for data storage and processing, as well as for flexibility. Overcoming their shortcomings has led to the implementation of new data models. NoSQL databases are not based on, or at least do not firmly adhere to, a relational model. In addition, they are easily distributed, horizontally scalable, and the value structure is usually not strictly predefined. Graph NoSQL database as a data model uses data modeling in the form of graphs consisting of interconnected nodes. This paper presents the possibilities of applying a Similar-Task algorithm to compare performance between graph and relational database.'),
(3368, 0, 0, 8, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Tomislav Unkašević', 1, 'Entity identification and security solutions in IoT based on PKI and Blockchain technology', 'Internet of things, Blockchain, digital identity,digital certificate digital signature', 'In networked information systems security basic problem is reliable entity identification and trustworthy system history creation. This is especially challenging task in the networks with computationally constrained devices like Internet of Things (IoT) is. In this paper we considered standard approaches to these problems, standard X.509 certificates and log files, showed that they are not appropriate for IoT and suggest solutions that better fit to IoT. Suggested solutions are applied in Institute VLATACOM current projects.'),
(3369, 0, 0, 11, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mihajlo Travar', 1, 'Razvoj softvera kao podrška razvoju turizma u Republici Srpskoj', 'Industrija turizama; Softverska rješenja; Digitalna transformacija; IKT; Globalizacija.', 'Informacione tehnologije danas imaju presudnu ulogu u efikasnom polovanju svih vertikala biznisa i donose nove modele poslovanja kojima se učesnici na tržištu prilagođavaju. Osnovni ciljevi informacionih sistema je omogućiti veću dostupnosti informacija, umrežavanje na globalnom nivou i ostvarenje većeg profita. Za turizam kao privrednu granu koja u osnovi svog poslovanja ima krajnjeg kupca, nije pitanje da li će već u kolikoj mjeri ući u procese digitalne transformacije. Informacione tehnologije treba da omoguće kolaboraciju između turista i pružaoca turističkih usluga. Postoje različiti alati pomoću kojih pružaoci turističkih usluga nastoje doći do turista od kojih se većina zasniva na web tehnologijama. Svakako ovaj proces ide u dva pravca, jedan podrazumijeva korišćenje tehnologije okrenute prema turistima a drugi korišćenje tehnologije radi bolje unutrašnje organizacije poslovnaja.'),
(3370, 1, 0, 7, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Sara Havzi', 1, 'Development of the MES software and Integration with an existing ERP Software in Industrial Enterprise', 'ERP, MES, industry systems management', 'The improvement of the processes within the production system is the need of each company in order to enable better monitoring and control, as well as to provide all real-time information that is important for the decision-making process, in order to improve all processes and simultaneously control all elements of the process. Some of the most known systems that provide process monitoring are Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) and Manufacturing Execution Systems (MES) systems, but usually, they are not integrated well, or company uses only one or none of those systems. This paper aims to show an example of the software solution that is integrated as a new MES system with an already existing ERP system in a single automotive industry.'),
(3371, 0, 1, 11, 'VRT', '2020', 1, 1, 'Ivan Boban', 1, 'Fleet management sustav implementiran kao SaaS s telekomunikacijskim aspektom primjene', 'fleet management, softver kao usluga–SaaS, telekom operateri, GPS, SIM, cloud', 'Mnoštvo današnjih softverskih rješenja se mogu nuditi kao usluga, odnosno SaaS (Software as a Service - Softver kao usluga). Jedan od takvih softverskih rješenja jeste i usluga Fleet managementa (FM) koja je visoko tehnološka platforma koja nudi mogućnost kompletnog upravljanja i logističke kontrole voznog parka. FM sustav se sastoji od više različitih modula i kao takav nudi niz funkcionalnosti, a jedan od glavnih modula je svakako komunikacijski modul s kojim FM sustav prikuplja različite parametre, obrađuje ih i šalje u centralni sustav. FM sustav je sustav koji može biti implementiran u okviru telekom operatera na način, da se taj isti sustav nudi kao usluga od strane telekoma, pogotovo zbog činjenice da telekom inače mora pružati infrastrukturu toj softverskoj platformi kako bi ona funkcionirala. Tu se u prvom redu misli na GSM sustav kojim se u realnom vremenu razmjenjuju podaci između vozila i centralnog sustava s tim da je veliki izazov kod ovakvih sustava riješiti razmjenu podataka u roamingu bez velikih troškova podatkovnog prometa. FM sustav kao takav, bez obzira na proizvođača tog sustava, nudi mogućnost kompletnog nadzora voznog parka sa svim funkcionalnostima i logističkom potporom. FM sustavi također imaju mogućnost integracije i s drugim sustavima u okviru implementacije zajedno s obračunskim sustavima, platformama za servisne narudžbe i slično. Glavni cilj rada je da se uz već poznate koncepte implementacije FM sustava, predstave i modeli primjene FM sustava kao SaaS, s naglaskom na integraciju s internim sustavima telekom operatera koji osiguravaju komercijalnu primjenu ovog sustava. U radu su predstavljeni koncepti kojima se pojašnjava na koji način se postojeća infrastruktura telekom operatera i obračunski sustavi  mogu iskoristiti kako bi se FM sustav mogao pružati kao usluga u okviru Cloud platformi.'),
(3372, 0, 0, 1, 'RSS-2', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'SQL Server to JSON', 'Microsoft SQL Server', 'This paper discuss extracting large and complex data sets from Microsoft SQL Server and converting them to hierarchical JSON file, while paying attention on data types, arrays and structure.'),
(3373, 1, 0, 1, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Marija Blagojević', 1, 'Orchestration of different services for predicting patient comfort during transport', 'transport, comfort, prediction, services, orchestration', 'The research presents the starting point for orchestration of different types of services in order to get precise information about patient comfort prediction during transport. The orchestration supposes these services: Google transport with GPS, Artificial intelligence service, Meteorological service, Vibration detection services. The architecture of orchestration was presented. Also, future work was highlighted.'),
(3374, 0, 0, 3, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Tamara Naumovic', 1, 'Development of the Continuous System Simulation Engine in Python Programing Language', 'continuous system simulation, python, engine, smart systems, IoT', 'This paper portrays the development of an simulation engine in Python programming language with focus on the continuous system simulation. Features of the engine are based on CSMP block-oriented language and software for continuous system simulation. The aim of the paper is threefold. Firstly, the paper describes the need and usage of such engine. Second goal is to analyze Python concepts used for the implementation of the simulation engine – API development, communication with smart systems, real- time data processing, integration of differential equations, threading and parallel programming. And last, this paper will depict the engine architecture, use cases and usage of the analyzed concepts in the development process. In the conclusion, we will discuss the overall outcome and the course of the future improvements and upgrades of the engine.'),
(3375, 1, 0, 4, 'P-3', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Improve code quality through the use of unit tests', 'unit test; agile approach; software maintenance; code quality', 'Today, companies are increasingly use an agile approach to software development. Unlike the software development approach known as waterfall, an agile approach leads to more procedures and clearly defined steps that need to be followed. These steps and procedures affect the very way of software implementation, and its development from the beginning until the final product, but also its maintenance. In larger companies that develop more complex software, later maintenance is very important. As important as it is for the software to be delivered on time and to meet the expected results, it is so important that it is designed so that it can be easily maintained, without making many mistakes, which means that it is understandable to all who participated in its creation, but also to those who will work to maintain it. To achieve this, software needs to be tested during development. There are a number of ways to test software, and one of them is to create unit tests (UT). The following section will describe in more detail how unit tests affect the quality of code during implementation and later in the system maintenance phase.'),
(3376, 0, 0, 8, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nenad Petrovic', 1, 'Ontology-Driven Generation of Interactive 3D Worlds', '3D graphics; ontology; semantics; simulation; video games; Three.js', 'In this paper, the ontology-driven approach to automated generation of interactive 3D applications is presented. The ontologies describing both static and dynamic application properties combined with domain-specific knowledge are leveraged. The approach is evaluated in two case studies: smart city simulator and virtual robotics testbed. The generated output is JavaScript code using Three.js library. According to the achieved results, the adoption of ontologies dramatically speeds up the development time compared to manual process.'),
(3377, 0, 0, 11, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Stefan Božanić ', 1, 'PID regulacija temperature prostorije preko Interneta Android aplikacijom', 'IoT, MQTT, Android, PID', 'The exchange of information among different devices and their management over the Internet tends to become necessary thing for a modern man. In this work is presented a practical implementation of PID regulators for remote control and supervising the temperature in the room via the Internet using the MQTT protocol. Using NodeMCU platform with WiFi  antenna and the temperature\'s sensors it is shown the relay\'s control and scale reading the current temperature in the room. In this work is being shown the concept of work of PID regulators, MQTT protocol and its practical realization of the mentioned hardware, which is being controlled via the Internet.'),
(3378, 0, 0, 3, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Zdravko Krpic', 1, 'Towards a synthetic load generator framework for validating schedules in HPC environment', 'High performance computing; scheduling; graph-based parallel workloads; DAG', 'Most of the scientific parallel and distributed applications require significant amount of time to complete on huge and expensive computing systems. Often, these applications are executed multiple times, making their scheduling a critical process for the runtime performance. One way to validate effectiveness of a schedule is to run the application on the actual hardware, which takes a lot of time and resources and is largely unfeasible. In this work we present a baseline for an adjustable-scale graph-based parallel workload executor framework for executing custom-scaled parallel applications given as graphs using synthetic load for the tasks, the GRAPPLER. The idea behind GRAPPLER is to operate as a schedule validator whose execution traces can provide valuable insights into runtime bottlenecks of the application, platform and the scheduler.'),
(3379, 0, 1, 8, 'VRT', '2020', 1, 1, 'Sara Gračić', 1, 'Test Process Improvement Through Test Maturity Models, Test Process Quality, Embedded Systems and DevSecOps Movement: A Tertiary Study', 'test process improvement; test maturity models; SLR; quality; embedded software', 'The quality of developed software is especially influenced by the quality of test processes. The purpose of this study was to give answer to research questions regarding quality, topics and trends in the field of test process improvement. To determine the-state-of-the-art achievements in the above mentioned field, it was necessary to summarize existing body of knowledge by conducting a tertiary study. 5 scientific databases were chosen; search string, inclusion, exclusion and quality criteria were defined and applied and the search resulted in 9 final papers. All sources reported the phenomenon of test process improvement from different perspectives: test maturity models, quality of testing process (test breakages, test smells and software quality management), embedded systems and DevSecOps movement.'),
(3380, 0, 0, 1, 'RSS-2', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Possibilities and perspectives of applying the e-learning model in educational institutions in Bosnia and Herzegovina', 'digital content; digital literacy; online platforms; virtual reality, virtual learning environment', 'E-learning is a type of learning by using electronic technologies to access an educational program outside\r\nof a traditional classroom. As conventional classrooms continue to be transformed into digital, it is\r\nnecessary for teachers to deliver lectures through multiple learning modes. Digitally enriched content and\r\npersonal learning should be the primary way of teaching, as well as collaborative and interactive learning.\r\nThe paper deals with issues of education in a virtual environment, the role of virtual reality and artificial\r\nintelligence that is increasingly entering the classrooms of developed countries. The paper explores what application of artificial intelligence in the near future means for the development and wider application of\r\nelectronic learning in virtual classrooms around the world, as well as in developing countries such as\r\nBosnia and Herzegovina. The paper presents the advantages and opportunities that contribute to the improvement of e-learning in educational institutions and the benefits for students and other involved parties in the educational process, such as teachers and parents.'),
(3381, 0, 0, 2, 'RSS-2', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Software model for recommending optimal performance database management system', 'Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, MSSQL, MYSQL, POSTGRESQL, SQL Query, SQL Query Performance, DB Server, Auto.ML, ML.NET.', 'Many times when users access the Web page they feel that the page is running fairly slowly. Also, when developing an application, developers find themselves in slowly loading pages. Very often hardware components were replaced in order to speed up the Web site, but it did not give the desired results. The problem was different. Retrieving data from the database was very slow. Often the problem is the complexity of queries that are executed, insufficient hardware resources, non-optimized code, etc. The subject of this research is the analysis, presentation and comparison of situations in which the use of machine learning is needed to find the optimal solution.'),
(3382, 0, 0, 3, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Boris Damjanović ', 1, 'Information security in m-learning systems: Challenges and Threats of using Cookies', 'information security; m-learning; cookies; privacy', 'The trend of rapid development of mobile technologies has highlighted new challenges and threats regarding the information security by the using cookies in mobile learning (m-learning) systems. In order to overcome these challenges and threats, this paper has identified two main objectives. First, to give a review of most common types to cookies and second, to consider the challenges and threats regarding cookies with aspects that are directly related to issues of security and privacy. With these objectives is possible to bridge security gaps in m-learning systems. Moreover, the identified potential challenges and threats are discussed with the given proposals of pragmatic solutions for their mitigating or reducing. The findings of this research may help students to rise security awareness and security behavior in m-learning systems, and to better understand on-going security challenges and threats in m-learning systems.'),
(3383, 1, 0, 8, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 1, 'Darko Kovačević', 1, 'Creation of Online Courses in ESP and their Use and Application in the Teaching Process', 'ESP, online course, creation, Course Builder, application, teaching process', 'Due to numerous reasons, online courses might appear as significant and valuable addition to the teaching of English for Special Purposes (ESP). In making an online course, Google\'s Course Builder application presents a free, practical and versatile tool which, at the same time, appears as easy and logical to use and offers an abundant set of possibilities and options for the creation of a course. After discussing the general concept and issues of ESP in the introduction, the Course Builder application will be described in the central part of the paper, in terms of its installation, features, components and course building options. Subsequently, the opportunities for the use and application of online courses created with the Course Builder application will be presented, both in terms of classroom use and extracurricular use. In the final part of the paper, some general conclusions will be made.'),
(3384, 0, 0, 12, 'KST', '2020', 1, 1, 'Saša Milić', 1, 'Industrijski internet stvari (IIoT) – strategije i koncepti', 'reči-industrijski internet stvari, komunikacioni protokoli, koncepti IIoT-a', 'Rad se u osnovi bavi aplikativnom primenom „industrijskog interneta stvari – IIoT“. Koncepti povezivanja „pametnih“ uređaja, uz primenu većeg broja standardnih komunikacionih protokola i pristupnih mrežnih tačaka, omogućavaju rad nad podacima u „oblaku“ u kome se vrše analize, procene, obrade, planiranje,... uz primenu velikog broja metoda, algoritama i strategija. U radu je dat detaljan pregled i osnovne karakteristike, danas najkorišćenijih komunikacionih i zaštitnih protokola koji su primenljivi u IoT-u i IIoT-u. Sa praktičnog aspekta, prikazane su dve koncepcije IIoT-a. Prva koncepcija, nazvana „otvorena koncepcija“ je standardna koncepcija IIot-a. Druga koncepcija, nazvana „poluotovrena koncepcija“ treba da omogući pouzdaniji rad industrijskog pogona sa aspekta onemogućavanja zlonamernog pristupa merenim podacima i da onemogući pokušaje promena i degradiranja proizvodnih parametara.'),
(3385, 0, 0, 5, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Almir Karabegovic', 1, 'Online Atlas as Decision Support System for Biomass Potential Assessment', 'online atlas; decision support system; biomass potential assessment; web geographic information systems', 'This paper shows how to integrate data from enterprise database with spatial data, publish them together to online interactive map, and enable public users to perform analysis in simple web interface. The fact, that this is a public site, where users are not known in advanced and not trained, calls for importance of usability and intuitive user interface design. Also, system administrators are not willing to invest a lot of time in learning the basics of a system, and data providers need effective geoportals to enable access to spatial data and services via the Internet. All these needs should be reconciled during the implementation of the solution. Due to increasing interest of forestry and agricultural organizations in spatial data infrastructure (SDI) development and public users’ needs for biomass data web presentation and analysis in Bosnia and Herzegovina, as case study is used the project of Biomass Potential Database with Online Atlas development. In addition, it is proposed application of the geoportal using online atlas as spatial decision support tool.');
INSERT INTO `rad` (`id`, `poster`, `virtual`, `rb`, `sesija`, `simpozijum`, `prihvacen`, `prezentovan`, `prezentovao`, `objavljen`, `naslov`, `k_rijeci`, `sazetak`) VALUES
(3386, 1, 0, 2, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Marko Bojkić', 1, 'Usage of Dependency Injection within different frameworks', 'Inversion of Control, Dependency Injection, Framework, Spring, Angular, Design pattern', 'During the development of applications, it is desirable\r\nto provide loose coupling of their components, so that\r\nprogram could be flexible, testable and maintainable. Within this paper, a design pattern is explained, which complies with the above requirements. Dependency Injection (DI), as one of the mechanisms for achieving the Inversion of Control (IoC) principle, represents a design pattern by which a particular class requires dependency on external sources, rather than creating it\r\nitself. Also, the usage of DI within the two different frameworks is presented, through the concrete examples presented in the code.'),
(3387, 1, 0, 3, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Uloga Web platformi i servisa kod izrade IoT aplikacija', 'IoT aplikacije, REST servis, WEB platforme', 'Svakog dana Internet postaje jedan globalni medijum na kome se sve više odvija komunikacija ne samo između ljudi već i različitih fizičkih objekata. Svi oni imaju sposobnost da sakupljaju veliku količinu različitih podataka i da iste potpuno samostalno razmenjuju između sebe. Pojam Internet of things postaje sve veći fenomen kojim se bavi veoma veliki broj istraživača i područje koje obećava rešavanje mnogih problema koji su vekovima mučili čovečanstvo. Sa jedne strane izgleda da je izrada jedne IoT aplikacije jako složen posao ali u suštini to nije tako. Veliki broj već razvijenih softverskih platformi kao i odgovarajući Web servisi u mnogome olakšavaju izradu jedne IoT aplikacije. Ovaj rad na praktičnom primeru pokazajuje koje sve prednosti programeri mogu da očekuju od korišćenja Web servisa kao i od mnogih Web platformi prilikom izrade IoT aplikacija.'),
(3388, 1, 0, 4, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Zoran Veličković', 1, 'Integracija Web API reCAPTCHA tehnologije na Web stranicu', 'Softverski robot. reCAPTCHA. Tjuringov test. Web API.', 'U ovom radu je prikazana zaštita Web stranice od napada malicioznog automatizovanog softvera na HTML forme. Forme su dizajnirane za rad sa čovekom. Maliciozni softver može imitirati rad ljudi na formi i time izazvati probleme u funkcionisanju Web stranice. Zbog toga je izuzetno važno sprečiti automatizovani softver da pristupi Web formama. U ovom radu je primenjena besplatna Guglova tehnologija - reCAPTCHA kojom se ustanovljava da li se radi o čoveku ili automatizovanom softveru. Za integraciju reCAPTCHA-e na Web stranicu koristi se Web API razvijen od strane Gugla. Analiza rezultata izvršenog Tjuringovog testa obavlja se na serverskoj strani Web aplikacije korišćenjem PHP skripta. Jednostavna integracija i pouzdan test reCAPTCHA tehnologiju preporučuju za korišćenje u visoko pouzdanim Web stranicama za zaštitu od napada automatizovanog softvera.'),
(3389, 0, 0, 12, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Elmir Babovic', 1, 'Further decrease of PC-to-PC SCADA implementation costs using credit-card sized computers', 'PC-to-PC SCADA, artificial intelligence in remote control, credit-card sized PC', 'In this research, authors proposed extension of the PC-to-PC SCADA concept, by using credit card sized computers. PC-to-PC SCADA concept decreases total SCADA implementation cost by replacing expensive sophisticated PLC\'s on RTU side, and replacing them with inexpensive general -purpose PC configuration, thus decreasing total implementation costs as well as enabling the system to include sophisticated control software with elements or artificial intelligence on remote side. This research further improves this concept by proposing to replace RTU side with credit-card sized computers with custom hardware interface in order to controls the object/target device.'),
(3390, 1, 0, 5, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Tanja Krunić', 1, 'A Responsive Web Design Testing Tool Using a Simulator  of Different Screen Shapes Built in JavaScript', 'screen shape; simulator, responsive web design; testing tool; JavaScript', 'The market of LED displays is growing worldwide. They appear in more and more different shapes and can be connected to computes. This means that they can be used for displaying web pages. Adapting web content for various screen shapes is going to be an upcoming issue in the field of responsive web design. Herein a responsive web design testing tool using a screen shape simulator is presented. The tool is built in JavaScript and is available on GitHub.'),
(3391, 0, 0, 8, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Dejan Vujičić', 1, 'Angular and Jenkins Based System for Remote Execution of Tasks on Raspberry Pi Cluster', 'cluster; Raspberry Pi; Angular; Jenkins; continuous integration; remote execution', 'This paper presents the system for remote execution of tasks on the Raspberry Pi cluster. The cluster consists of four Raspberry Pi 3 modules. The frontend Angular application is created for user interaction with the system, using web services. Jenkins is responsible for continuous integration and serves as an interconnection between the frontend application and the cluster. We demonstrated the successful execution of the Python script residing on the cluster.'),
(3392, 1, 0, 1, 'P-3', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'IMPLEMENTATION OF MACHINE LEARNING ALGORITHMS IN THE IOT ENVIRONMENT TO HELP PERSONS WITH REDUCED PSYCHOMOTORY ABILITIES', 'Machine Learning, IoT, Algoritmhs, help, software', 'Learning and understanding have always been characteristics that are thought to be inherent in humans, possibly individual animals, and the possibility that a machine can learn for a long time has not been intrusive. Understanding the learning process and how to program a machine to learn can have significant implications for machines and humans. The realization that biological organisms have particular characteristics of so-called &#039;machines&#039; is not alien, thus the learning machine becomes acceptable. The possibilities are diverse and interesting: effective treatments in medicine, diagnostics in general, the so-called smart environment (homes, airports, hospitals, ...), communication, robots, hearing and vision are many examples. Natural language algorithms, traffic applications developed to enable machine learning have feedback, provide insight into learning opportunities and learning processes of biological organisms. The development of machine learning is fast and covers multiple fields. A major theme within this field of work is its application in healthcare and assistance to people in need of health care. With this thinking and the goal of making it possible, the current breakthroughs in technology fields allow for it. IoT and machine learning are an ideal match. The work is so conceptual that in the first chapters it draws a picture of these concepts of IoT and Machine Learning with a turn to practical examples in everyday life. There are so many things around us that we are not aware of how it works and that it is part of what is being learned in this work. One is medicine. Medicine deals with the diagnosis, prevention and treatment of physical and mental illness of man.\r\nToday, medicine relies a lot on computer technology, machine learning is used to identify abnormalities at an early stage. Accurate diagnosis is very important for deciding on the right therapy. But in many cases it is very difficult for the doctor to identify the patient&#039;s level. Using clinical records, machine learning methods can be used to produce a descriptive analysis of clinical characteristics. Machine learning algorithms are widely used in the diagnosis of various diseases such as diabetic retinopathy, heart problems, cancer.'),
(3393, 0, 0, 8, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'LJUBOMIR LAZIĆ', 1, 'Obrada velikih količina podataka u Hadoop ekosistemu', 'Big data; Hadoop; MapReduce; ETL proces; MySQL', 'U ovom radu se opisuje jedno rešenje obrade velikih količina podataka pomoću Hadoop ekosistema u odnosu na tradicionalne baze podataka na primeru fiktivnih transakcija sajta za e-kupovinu. U radu se najpre teorijski obrađuje skladištenje i obrada velikih količina podataka, arhitektura i komponente Hadoop klastera, njegova konfiguracija i primena MapReduce tehnike na njemu. Zatim se, na praktičnom primeru prikazuje nadmoć Hadoop sistema prilikom izvlačenja statističkih podataka iz 3 tabele različitih veličina (1, 10 i 100 miliona transakcija) koje su smeštene u okviru jedne MySQL baze podataka. Na kraju su prikazani rezultati dobijeni merenjima i njihova analiza, kao i zaključci eksperimenta.'),
(3394, 0, 0, 1, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Esad KADUSIC', 1, 'Directed Acyclic Graph as Hashgraph: an Alternative DLT to Blockchains and Tangles', 'Hashgraph; Hash Function; Distributed Ledger Technologies', 'Distributed Ledger Technologies are one of the pillars of future technologies, prognozing to have a great impact to many aspects of our lives, including social, economic, juristic, security and many others. Bitcoin is still the most popular blockchain currency, but the opportunities to use Distribute Ledger Technologies are much more wide, outperforming financial applications as most known and popular. Besides blockchains, there are also other architectures of Distributed Ledger Technologies. This paper observes and analyses one technology as a very strong alternative to blockchains: hashgraphs, which are promising to outperform blockchains, but also tangles. Basis of their architecture and functionality will be explained and directions and prognosis of the further development will be given. The main paper contribution is a comparison of a hashgraph technology to its concurrent architectures, i.e. blockchains and tangles, considering different segments and different properties that define a quality of  Distributed Ledgers.'),
(3395, 0, 0, 2, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Milana Grbić', 1, 'Partitioning Weighted Metabolic Networks into Maximally Balanced Connected Partitions', 'partitioning metabolic networks; variable neighborhood search; maximally balanced partitioning problem', 'Partitioning biological network into smaller components can help in retrieving new information of a particular biological structure. In this research we investigate the problem of partitioning node-weighted metabolic networks into two maximally balanced connected components. The problem of partitioning networks into maximally balanced connected components (MBCP) is an NP hard problem. We apply a variable neighborhood search metaheuristic algorithm for solving MBCP on several metabolic networks and provide experimental results which can be useful for further biological interpretation.'),
(3396, 1, 0, 1, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 1, 'Marijana Cosovic', 1, 'CNN Classification of the Cultural Heritage Images', 'cultural heritage; image classification; machine learning, deep neural networks', 'The cultural heritage image classification represents one of the most important tasks in the process of digitalization. In this paper, a deep learning neural network was applied in order to classify images of architectural heritage belonging to ten categories, in particular: (i) bell tower, (ii) stained glass, (iii) vault, (iv) column, (v) outer dome, (vi) altar, (vii) apse, (viii) inner dome, (ix) flying buttress, and (x) gargoyle. The Convolutional neural network was used for image classification, with the same architecture applied on two sets of the data: the full dataset consisting of 10 categories as well as dataset with 5 different image categories. The results show that both architectures performed well and obtained accuracy of up to 90%.'),
(3397, 0, 0, 3, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Elmir Babovic', 1, 'Prediction of mortality in patients with cardiovascular disease using data mining methods', 'data mining, healthcare analytics, predicting, decision tree, neural networks, logistic regression', 'Healthcare information systems store a huge amount of patient data, so the trend of the use of data mining in healthcare is on the rise. Heart and blood vessel diseases are a leading cause of mortality both worldwide and here in Bosnia and Herzegovina, and prevention, surveillance and treatment are of great public health importance. Based on data on patients with cardiovascular disease, collected from 2011 to 2017 at Mostar Hospital, models for mortality prediction using techniques for data tree mining, neural network and logistic regression are presented. The aim of this research is to compare the effectiveness of these methods in modeling the effectiveness of predicting mortality in patients with cardiovascular disease.'),
(3398, 1, 0, 2, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Wireless Channel Prediction using Least Squares Support Vector Machines', 'channel prediction; least squares support vector machines; microcellular environment; picocellular environment', 'This paper proposes application of least squares support vector machines (LS-SVMs) for prediction of wireless channel conditions of single-input single-output (SISO) systems in microcellular and picocellular environments. For performance measure normalized mean squared error (NMSE) and time consumption are used. The experimental results show high accuracy and short execution time of the LS-SVM prediction model on measured values for signal-to-noise ratio (SNR).'),
(3399, 1, 0, 3, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 1, 'Branislava Cvijetić', 1, 'Primjena mašinskog učenja u procesu klasifikacije oglašenih radnih mjesta', 'veliki podaci; mašinsko nadgledano učenje; klasifikacija tekstualnih podataka; obrada govornog jezika', 'Institucije koje proizvode službene statistike teže da što više, pored redovnih statističkih istraživanja, primjenjuju eksterne izvore podataka, kao što su administrativni izvori podataka. Osim navedenih izvora podataka, veliki podaci su takođe prepoznati kao novi izvori podataka. Jedan od osnovnih zadataka u statistici, bez obzira o kom izvoru podataka je riječ, jeste automatska klasifikacija tekstualnih podataka. U ovom radu korišćeni su algoritmi mašinskog učenja nad podacima prikupljenim sa četiri veb sajta, a sve u cilju da se provjeri uspješnost primjene algoritama mašinskog učenja prilikom automatske klasifikacije tekstualnih nestrukturiranih podataka.'),
(3400, 0, 0, 9, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Duško Sivčević', 1, 'Possibilities of used intelligence based agents in instant messaging on e-government services', 'Intelligent agent; chabot; artificial intelligence (AI); QA application', 'This paper investigated technical possibilities of delivery and deployment of Government e-services in Republic of Serbia that will enable citizens and business sector to simplify exercising right and fulfill obligation to the state authorities completely on line. These e-services for data resource use data records contained in the Data Base Management Systems (DBMS) in responsibility of the Ministry of Interior (MOI). We will describe and show practical model for the motivation, objectives and overview of an intelligent Decision Support System (DSS) related to usage of web technologies in process of intelligent search of large amounts of data. Based on research results we will present a conceptual solution for usage of interactive instant messaging application in process of giving answers to the questions by side of police authorities in their daily interaction with citizens and business community.'),
(3401, 0, 0, 4, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Dijana Kosmajac', 1, 'Language Distance using Common N-Grams Approach', 'Language Distance; Linguistic Distance; Language Identification; Natural Language Processing (NLP); European languages; Common N-Grams;', 'Within the framework of historical linguistics, the prevailing view of the linguistic experts is that language similarity cannot be measured. However, there has been significant research to attempt to quantify this phenomenon. We extend experiments conducted by Gamallo et al. from 2017 to compare forty-one European languages. We use a distance measure that was proven to work well in authorship attribution tasks. We build a distance network where the nodes represent the languages, and the weighted edges represent distances. We additionally provide statistical analysis that confirms the stability of our method across different experimental setups.'),
(3402, 0, 0, 11, 'RSS-2', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'eAgro - Predicting Plant Water and Soil Ingredients Requirements', 'agriculture, eAgro, soil analysis, fertilization, toolset, web platform', 'This paper describes in detail the development of a tool to be implemented in a future web platform called eAgro. The web platform will serve for all members of agriculture to promote themselves and their products, to create a thriving environment for businesses and to serve as an organizing tool in the large community of agricultural workers. The tool discussed in this paper analyses the weather conditions of an area, coupled with the soil analysis of land to give predictions and suggestions for crop growth and fertilization, using elements of data science and developed formulas. The paper contains the motivation for the idea, a detailed explanation of the methodology used and the future potential of such a tool.'),
(3403, 0, 0, 9, 'RSS-2', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'eAgro - Automatic Weed Detection Tool Development', 'Agriculture, Weed detection, Digitalization, Tools, Improvement, Application', 'The goal of this project is to digitalize, and improve the agriculture industry in our own region, in the Republic of Serbia. Agriculture is largely involved in Serbia\'s financial state, with the potential to be one of the main sources of revenue. Unfortunately, it lacks structure and innovation. Once we understood the significance and the importance it has on our economy, we have decided to develop an application that would tackle these issues with specialized tools and services that we would provide to our user in an elegant and easy to use interface. The solutions are developed, by following the needs of our customers and the ever-changing new trends of the industry. The tool we created is used for weed detection, enabling farmers to easily locate it and remove it. \r\nIn this document, the details of our current state of development, our ideas, implementations, functionalities, motivations and plans for the future are presented.'),
(3404, 0, 0, 13, 'RSS-2', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Analiza atributa potrebnih za predikciju posledica zagađenja vazduha u kotlinama', 'atributi zagađenja vazduha; pravila odlučivanja, redukt skupa', 'Zagađenje vazduha se meri godinama unazad i na osnovu različitih metodologija računaju se granice zagađenja. Merene vrednosti opasnih materija su najvažniji atributi koje mere agencije i drugi subjekti. Često se posmatraju podaci za određenu regiju i za određeni period. Zbog povećanja temperature vazduha posebno su aktulna merenja zagađenja vazduha u kotlinama. Nad podacima zagađenja vazduha, teorijom grubih skupova pokazan je način generisanja redukta podataka kao i pravila odlučivanja. Analizirani su atributi koji bi mogli da daju preciznije predikcije posledica zagađenja vazduha u kotlinama. Rad je potkrepljen primerom.'),
(3405, 1, 0, 4, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 1, 'Jasmina Novakovic', 1, 'Performance of Support Vector Machine in Imbalanced Data Set', 'accuracy; classification; imbalanced data set; kernel function; SVM', 'This paper considers the problem of an imbalanced data set, in which one class has a significantly larger number of samples than the other. Since it is necessary to determine as accurately as possible the classification accuracy of a class that has a small number of samples, different methods are used in the paper to measure the performance of the classifier. We used real data set obtained from the transaction through a payment card, in which a certain number of transactions was generated by unauthorized persons. SVM algorithm was used for classification, with the best operating parameters determined during cross-validation. The paper presents the results obtained for measuring the performance of SVM algorithm.'),
(3406, 0, 0, 6, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Emir Cogo', 1, 'Position based visualization of real world warehouse data in a smart warehouse management system', 'data visualization; smart warehouse management system; visual analytics; warehouse optimization; picking zone, warehouse layout', 'This paper presents a data visualization method in 3D space that includes actual positions, volumes and space relations of the chunks of data that are being visualized. Data that is being visualized is real-time information provided by the smart warehouse management system about packages distributed on pallet places within a warehouse. Three different visualizations are shown: qualitative, quantitative and cumulative. The method is graded for the time needed to determine the location of all pallet places that fulfill searched criteria and getting the exact value of searched information for each pallet place. Challenges in presenting this data and interacting with resulting visualizations are discussed. It is concluded that showing actual positions of chunks of data greatly increases the speed of acquiring searched values and positions at the same time for outliers but has issues with clusters and multiple types of queried data.'),
(3407, 0, 1, 16, 'VRT', '2020', 1, 1, 'Aldina Avdić', 1, 'Kreiranje resursa za obeležavanje dijagnoza u medicinskim izveštajima na srpskom jeziku', 'medicinski izveštaji; dijagnoze; automatsko označavanje; kompjuterska obrada teksta; leksički resursi', 'U ovom radu je prikazano kreiranje medicinskih leksičkih resursa za automatsko označavanje termina iz dijagnoza u medicinskim izveštajima. Da bi se izvršilo automatsko označavanje slobodnog teksta potrebne su metode komjuterske obrade prirodnih jezika kao i odgovarajući leksički resursi. Kako ne postoje javno dostupni medicinski leksički resursi za srpski jezik, kao ni korpus sa medicinskim izveštajima, doprinos ovog rada je izgradnja  ovakvih resursa za potrebe automatskog obeležavanja dijagnoza.'),
(3408, 0, 0, 5, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Seila Becirovic', 1, 'A Case Study of Cluster-based and Histogram-based Multivariate Anomaly Detection Approach in General  Ledgers', 'Anomaly detection, Cluster analysis, Histogram analysis, Financial data', 'The rapid development of financial markets results in data variability and unpredictability. Anomaly detection in financial data is a very important issue. Finding anomalies can result in error reduction and corrections in due time. The main aim of this research was to find anomalies in general ledgers of a real company in Bosnia and Herzegovina. Anomalies are defined as input errors of accountants. Main concepts of anomaly detection are defined, a summary of the current progress is given, and challenges of future work are presented. Cluster-based and histogram-based anomaly detections were performed on a real-life dataset of a microcredit organization. Results of algorithms were presented, as well as results achieved using synthetic data.'),
(3409, 0, 0, 6, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Predrag Milosav', 1, 'Minimal Decimal Difference Method Applied in Spatial Image Steganography', 'Spatial Image Steganography, LSB, Histogram, Image Processing, MSE, PSNR, SSIM', 'This paper deals with the improved method of spatial image steganography - Minimal Decimal Difference Method. The basic LSB method, as a starting point, was improved, an implementation algorithm was proposed and developed, and then measurements were made and results were processed. The benefits achieved by the advanced method in comparison with the classical LSB (Least Significant Bit) method are presented graphically and numerically and further research and development is proposed in order to achieve even better results.'),
(3410, 1, 0, 2, 'P-3', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Analiza medijske informisanosti na osnovu istraživanja o evaluaciji rada kancelarije Zaštitnika građana Novog Sada', 'mediji, ombudsman, javno mnjenje', 'U radu će biti prikazan pregled literature na temu odnosa građana prema različitim vrstama medija, uz prikaz i analizu, do sada ne objavljenih, rezultata istraživanja sprovedenog 2018. godine na temu «Informisanost i evaluacija rada kancelarije Zaštitnika građana Novog Sada». Deo istraživanje se odnosi na način informisanja, dostupnost informacija i njihovo razumevanje u odnosu na izbor medija informisanja, što će u radu biti posebno analizirano. Cilj istraživanja je da se pokaže značaj izbora medija za plasiranje medijskih poruka u odnosu na efekte i njihov uticaj na javno mnenje. Kontekst sve većeg uticaja informacionih tehnologija na sve aspekte našeg života, svakako utiče i na sam proces i pravo slobode informisanja u procesu komuniciranja, kao jednog od osnovnih prava svakog čoveka. Značaj izbora medija i načina plasiranja informacija kao jednan od elemenata uticanja na javno mnjenje zavređuje ovakav tip analize.'),
(3411, 1, 0, 3, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nataša Savić', 1, 'Performanse AGCWD algoritma za korekciju kontrasta kod slika u boji', 'procesiranje slike; kontrast; histogram; luminansa; hrominansa; HSV', 'U prvom delu rada opisani su algoritmi TGC, THE, AGC i AGCWD za korekciju kontrasta. U drugom delu rada opisan je eksperiment u kome je, primenom opisanih algoritama, vršena korekcija kontrasta kod slika u boji. Efikasnost algoritama određena je pomoću objektivnih mera za kvalitet kontrasta. Rezultati su prikazani pomoću slika i tabela. Na kraju je izvršena komparativna analiza. Analiza rezultata pokazala je da je AGCWD algoritam efikasniji u odnosu na TGC i AGC algoritme, dok je manje efikasan u odnosu na THE algoritam.'),
(3412, 0, 0, 1, 'RSS-3', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Beskontaktni sistem plaćanja na festivalima', 'Beskontaktni; sistem plaćanja; čitač; RFID kartice', 'Kako bi proces kupovine hrane, pića i suvenira na festivalima bio što brži, efikasniji i produktivniji, ulazimo u eru “cashless” i “contactless” sistema plaćanja. Beskontaktni sistemi plaćanja podrazumijevaju platne transakcije bez fizičkog kontakta između uređaja koji posjetilac koristi prilikom plaćanja i uređaja koji se nalazi na strani trgovca. Za plaćanje se koriste RFID kartice ili narukvice, na koje se uplaćuje željeni iznos novca na blagajni, dok se na prodajnim mjestima nalazi beskontaktni RFID čitač i aplikacija koja omogućava prodaju željenih artikala. Sistem kontroliše pozadinska aplikacija u koju se evidentiraju sve transakcije i koja daje mnoštvo izvještaja i statistika, te bogatu analitiku koja je naročito korisna za organizatore događaja. Ovi sistemi pojednostavljuju i ubrzavaju proces kupovine na festivalima i koncertima, te poboljšavaju kvalitet usluge i povećavaju zadovoljstvo posjetilaca.'),
(3413, 0, 0, 2, 'RSS-3', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Matematički model i vizualizacija signala u softveru Matlab', 'Matematički model, signal, prenosna funkcija, vizualizacija, Matlab', 'Matematički modeli za prikazivanje signala su veoma korisni alati koje možemo iskoristiti u različite svrhe . Ovi modeli mogu da se odnose na signale, podatke ili sisteme. Tokom rješavanja određenih problema potreban je neki softverski alat za testiranje ponasanja tih signala. U našem slučaju opredjelili smo se za inženjerski softver Matlab. Prikazivanje pomoću matematičkog modela zahtijeva poznavanje podataka tj. sistem mora da ima ulaz, prenosnu funkciju i izlaz. Prenosna funkcija najčešće je matematička funkcija definisana na određenom području. U slučaju linearnih stohastičkih sistema koristiti ćemo prijenos funkcije tj. jednačinu prostora stanja. Modeli vremenskih serija takođe bi bili upotrebljivi za ovo istraživanje. Zanimljivo bi bilo u svrhu ptredviđanja ponašanja određenih modela izvršiti kompresiju podatak kako bismo olakšali specifične aspekte predmeta proučavanja ovog rada. Matlab nam pruža ogromen mogučnosti za očitovanje konkretnih primjera koji ne zahtijevaju kompleksne linije koda'),
(3414, 0, 0, 5, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Ilja Stanišević', 1, 'Poređenje brzine odziva  MS SQL servera i MySQL-a', 'sistemi za upravljanje bazom podataka; Microsoft SQL Server; MySQL; benčmark testovi', 'U nameri da izaberemo optimalan sistem za upravljanje bazom podataka za informacioni sistem Visoke poslovne škole strukovnih studija VIPOS u Valjevu, izvršena su testiranja najpredlaganijih opcija (MS SQL Server i MySQL). Umesto oslanjanja na postojeće alate za testiranje – benchmarke, razvojni tim je razvio svoj alat koji je rađen u istoj tehnologiji kao i školski sistem i koji je namenjen testiranju onih aspekata koji su relevantni za konkretnu situaciju u kojoj se sistem realizovao. U ovom radu je opisana primenjena metodologija i način realizacije testnog alata, kao i dati prikaz ostvarenih rezultata.'),
(3415, 0, 0, 1, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Valentina Timcenko', 1, 'Comparing Hypervisor Virtualization Performance with the Example of Citrix Hypervisor (XenServer) and Microsoft Hyper-V', 'Microsoft Hyper-V; Citrix XenServer; Windows Server; virtual machine', 'This paper presents the comparison of two representatives of type 1 hypervisors: XenServer and Microsoft Hyper-V. With the help of HD Tune Pro, we compare the performance of the hypervisor. Both hypervisors were tested in the same conditions with the MS Windows Server as the guest operating system. The obtained results are in accordance with the defined hypotheses for the expected behavior of the hypervisors.'),
(3416, 0, 0, 5, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Goran Skondric', 1, 'Optimization of availability and resource utilisation in LAN based P2P storage distributed systems', 'P2P, storage distributed systems, simulation, digital file collection', 'Simulations of the desired system usually precede the development of P2P storage distributed systems. Justification for the development of the system is based on the results of simulations. Valid recognition of input parameters is essential for the quality output of such simulations.  We collected data from the Faculty of information technology network, about node presence and patter of file generation. We discovered a small group of users with a similar pattern of behavior and file generation. Based on analyzed data, we developed a user model for this user group with parameters, such as the average size of user files stored on their storage locations and the pattern of file generation.  After that, we compared the availability of a distributed storage system when using a coincidence matrix and a user clustering method, from our previous research. The aim of the research is to determine the moment of justification for using one of these two approaches in peer selection.'),
(3417, 0, 0, 10, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Dragana Bajić', 1, 'Temporal transformations of multivariable dependency structures', 'dependency structures; copula density; density estimation; cardiovascular time series;', 'This paper analyses an original transform of dependency structures of multivariable signals from the probabilistic to the temporal domain, Dependency structures are multidimensional probability densities that show the coupling strength of the observed signals. A corresponding mathematical model is ‘copula density’, a static concept defined within the probabilistic domain. The proposed dynamic model of coupling strength enables the analysis of temporal fluctuations of coupling strength. Such an analysis is of importance for medical applications, so cardiovascular signals of laboratory animals were analyzed. A key transformation parameter is copula density, so several estimation methods are compared.'),
(3418, 1, 0, 8, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mladen Knezic', 1, 'An Extension of a Linux UART Driver', 'driver; Linux; UART; serial interface', 'Embedded systems usually must communicate with many peripheral devices using a low-cost serial interfaces such as UART (Universal Asynchronous Receiver Transmitter). On the other end, a typical microcontroller used in such systems has a small number of UART interfaces exported to a user. In this paper, we describe an extension of a Linux UART driver that supports communication with multiple peripheral devices via single UART interface. The driver can be seamlessly integrated into the Linux architecture and requires minimum hardware changes.'),
(3419, 0, 0, 4, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nebojša Kuduz', 1, 'Building a Multitenant Data Hub System using Elastic Stack and Kafka for Uniform Data Representation', 'Elasticsearch; Kafka; Logstash; Kibana; Beats', 'The goal of this paper is to present one way of building and implementing of an Elastic Stack based System for processing data of various types and formats, events from custom applications and for transforming input data to be presented in a uniform way. For practical data hub system implementation, events and logs are collected from various IoT devices through LoRa WAN gateways, messaging gateways and management information subsystems. Data are shipped directly or using Beats. Logstash and Apache Kafka are used for processing and buffering of data streams, to execute different filters, for input data enhancements and transformations and for indexing and storing data into Elasticsearch. Kibana provides visualization capabilities on top of the content indexed by Elasticsearch. System is designed and configured as elastic multitenant solution to target different consumers by indices separated to different spaces and with role-based and attribute-based access controls.'),
(3420, 1, 0, 9, 'P-3', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Pregled definisanja i praćenja SLA za 5G servise', 'SLA; 5G; QoS; KPI; network slicing', 'U radu je opisan način definisanja i merenja kvaliteta 5G servisa kod ugovaranja usluga sa definisanim nivoom kvaliteta (SLA – Service Level Agreement). Jedna od glavnih karakteristika 5G mreža je koncept mrežnih slojeva (network slicing). Dok su prethodne generacije mobilnih mreža pružale servise svim tipovima korisnika kroz jedinstvenu mrežnu infrastrukturu, kod 5G je omogućeno pružanje servisa po mrežnim slojevima. Svaki servis, a time i odgovarajući mrežni sloj, treba da ispune određeni zahtev u pogledu konfiguracije i kvaliteta servisa (QoS). Stoga je u radu dat pregled na koji način je za različite aplikacije, koje koriste različite mrežne slojeve, moguće definisati i meriti ispunjenost SLA.'),
(3421, 0, 0, 5, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Edvin Teskeredžić', 1, 'Comparison of the Non-Blocked and Blocked Floyd-Warshall Algorithm with Regard to Speedup and Energy Saving on an Embedded GPU', 'APSP, CUDA, Optimization, Energy Consumption', 'In this paper, three variants of the Floyd-Warshall (FW) All Pairs Shortest Path (APSP) algorithm are presented and compared - the sequential implementation, the parallel implementation using the Nvidia CUDA API, and the blocked parallel version of the FW algorithm. A performance analysis between these three approaches, as well as between the individual phases of the parallel algorithm is provided. The performance of these algorithms has been measured on regular as well as on embedded GPU hardware, and a significant speedup has been achieved. Additionally, this paper shows that a blocked data access results in significant energy savings of up to 72% on embedded hardware.'),
(3422, 0, 0, 6, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Branko Livada', 1, 'Digital Medical Imaging Displays Specification: Understanding Technology Helps to Achieve High Quality in Image Interpretation', 'Digital medical imaging, dispalys, brightness, grayscale display function, luminance, display performance parameters, resolution, quality assesment, requirement definition, human visual system, perception of visual information', 'Digital medical imaging technology is developing rapidly in the last few decades and widely used as medical diagnostic tool. Medical image visual content analysis and interpretation is the most often method applied in detection and tracking of the pathogen behavior of the imaged tissue. The human visual perception of the displayed image is limited by human visual system properties, display device characteristics, illumination environment influences during observation. In this review article we are analyzing how medical image specificities, human eye visual properties and display technology ultimate performances could be used to define medical image monitor technical requirements according to named application. We are focused on the analysis of the physical processes involved and technical aspects leading to optimization of the medical display requirements definition. This will help engineering and medical specialists to understand better medical display properties and provide more objective assessment of the display diagnostic suitability.'),
(3423, 0, 0, 6, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Snežana Puzović', 1, 'Enhancement Algorithms for Low-Light and Low-Contrast Images', 'Image dehazing, low-light imaging, image enhancement, image quality assessment', 'Images in bad weather can be degraded by scattering atmospheric particles, and suffer from low contrast and faint color. Main focus of this work is on dehazing methods that can be used for low-light and low-contrast conditions. Dehazing algorithms can be applied to low-light imaging in a way that inverted low-light (night) images are considered as hazy images. Different image quality metrics are used to measure quality of image enhancement algorithm. Since it is not easy to obtain original image without haze, special attention is given to the no-reference metrics that evaluate image contrast enhancement'),
(3424, 1, 0, 9, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 1, 'Gordana Manojlović-Kovačević', 1, 'Primena tri Android aplikacije u nastavi solfeđa i teorije muzike u osnovnim muzičkim školama', 'Android, aplikacije, solfeđo, teorija muzike, Complete Music Reading Trainer, Complete Rhythm Trainer, Complete Ear Trainer, nastava', 'Razvoj informacionih tehnologija u današnje vreme kao jednu od značajnih posledica ima i snažno prisustvo pametnih telefona i tablet-računara, zasnovanih na operativnom sistemu Android i sa ekranima osetljivim na dodir, u gotovo svim sferama svakodnevnog delovanja. Takvo prisustvo se prvenstveno manifestuje kroz brojne aplikacije za ovakve uređaje, koje se, sa različitim namenama i usmerene ka različitim ciljnim grupama, pojavljuju gotovo svakodnevno, tako da sigurno nije moglo zaobići ni nastavu solfeđa i teorije muzike u osnovnim muzičkim školama. Zahvaljujući činjenici da su pametni telefoni i tablet-računari danas prisutni u većini domova, zatim pojavi da, naročito tokom poslednjih nekoliko godina, sve veći broj učenika poseduje vlastite uređaje ovog tipa, te, konačno, postojanju velikog broja edukativnih aplikacija za savladavanje i rešavanje različitih problema iz domena nastave solfeđa i teorije muzike, njihova upotreba, kako u nastavi, tako i u vannastavnim aktivnostima nameće se kao logično, praktično i korisno rešenje. Grupa od tri aplikacije: Complete Music Reading Trainer, Complete Rhythm Trainer i Complete Ear Trainer predstavlja sveobuhvatno rešenje za obradu i uvežbavanje različitih nastavnih jedinica i oblasti u okviru nastave solfeđa i teorije muzike u osnovnim muzičkim školama. Svaka od njih se bavi po jednim od suštinskih pitanja nastave solfeđa i teorije muzike (čitanje nota, ritam i razvoj slušnih sposobnosti) i, kroz različite vidove vežbanja, organizovanih postupno i na više mogućih nivoa, uz odgovarajuća teorijska poglavlja koja prethode samim vežbanjima, omogućava postupno usvajanje, uvežbavanje i savladavanje određenih jedinica, problema, a time i samog gradiva. U radu će biti predstavljene karakteristike i mogućnosti svake od tri navedene aplikacije, a potom i mogućnosti njihove praktične primene, kako u nastavi, tako i u vannastavnim aktivnostima vezanim za nastavu solfeđa i teorije muzike u osnovnim muzičkim školama.'),
(3425, 1, 0, 9, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Srdjan Tegeltija', 1, 'Universal IoT Vending Machine Management Platform', 'IoT; platform; management; vending machine;', 'Through the advancement of the technique, vending machines have evolved from simple devices to sell individual products and provide simple services to complex devices where product and service offerings are tailored to each individual user. The increasing need to use a large amount of information in real time (optimization of supply, timely updating of machines, monitoring the status of vending machines, etc) an increasing number of vending machines are connecting to the Internet and represents the IoT devices in the IoT ecosystem. In this paper a solution of a universal IoT platform for managing vending machines is proposed. Emphasis is placed on the implementation of the control unit with an additional module for interaction with the users.'),
(3426, 0, 0, 9, 'RSS-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Džemil Džigal', 1, 'Acceleration of the CUDA Implementation of the Grayscale and Negative Filters', 'image processing, parallel implementation, CUDA, Compiler-level Optimisation, Work Arrangement', 'Real-Time image processing is a difficult, labor-\r\nexpensive and challenging task using standard high-level Pro-\r\ngramming Languages such as C, C++, Java, C# and oth-\r\ners. Compiler-level Optimisation ensures some acceleration of\r\nexecution, but for the usual uses of Image Processing, such\r\noptimisations are not enough. Processors of the modern time\r\nassign the use of HyperThreading and similar technologies, to the\r\nextent that we can, without a reasonable doubt say that there\r\nare no truly sequential programs. Thus the parallel software\r\nis of the upmost importance to be written. After the optimal\r\nrearrangement of work for every worker in the system, code and\r\ncompiler-level optimization should be implemented for the final\r\ngoal of having an optimal parallel code, code and compiler-wise\r\nand work arrangement-wise.'),
(3427, 1, 0, 5, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 1, 'Miroslava Mihajlov Carević', 1, 'Dominating  sets  on  the  rhomboidal  cactus  chains  and the  icosahedral  network', 'dominating set, domination number, rhomboidal cactus chains, icosahedral hexagonal  network', 'In this paper, we deal with the dominating set and the domination number of rhomboidal cactus chains. We determine minimum dominating sets and domination numbers of two special types of rhomboidal cactus chains, meta and ortho-chains. Thereafter, we determined the minimum dominating set for the icosahedral hexagonal network'),
(3428, 1, 0, 7, 'P-4', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nikola Davidović', 1, 'The influence of workloads and depth queue on the performance of SSD disk RAID 0 level array', 'RAID 0, capacity, SSD disk, write speed, read speed, average workload data block, queue depth', 'The RAID 0 level represents a group of N independent disks. The data is written consecutively in blocks to various hardware units. This procedure increases the total storage space. Since the capacity of SSD devices is relatively small, connecting them into a N disks RAID 0 array results in a device N times larger than the smallest device. RAID 0 allows multiple devices to be accessed simultaneously, that is, to obtain write and read speed operations in proportion to the number of SSDs that are forming the array (if the bus speed allows). However, the performance of the RAID 0 array, besides the impact of the number of used units, is also affected by other parameters. The paper analyzes the effect of RAID 0 array size (number of SSD units), average block size, and queue depth to the RAID 0 array performance.'),
(3429, 0, 0, 10, 'RSS-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Snježana Maksimović', 1, 'Summation formulas using a new class of special polynomials', 'diferential equation, special polynomials, series, Wiener rational basis', 'In this paper we used a new class of special polynomials which satisfy a Sturm Liouvile diferential equation of second order. These polynomials form a basis of a polynomial space. Using coefficients of these polynomials we formed a lower triangular matrix which represents a transition matrix from standard polynomial basis to this new basis. Using Matlab for given natural number we obtained a corresponding matrix, found an inverse of this matrix, their eigenvalues and some interesting properties. Using a new class of special polynomials we obtained some interesting and usefull summation formulas.'),
(3430, 1, 0, 10, 'P-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Miljan Sikimić', 1, 'An Overview of Wireless Technologies for IoT Network', 'Internet of Things; communication; wireless; radio communication; comparative analysis;', 'The Internet of Things (IoT) is a concept of the modern, interconnected world. Over 50 billion devices, globally-connected, make up the largest network that is stepping towards the fourth industrial revolution, and which will significantly change the system of values and business systems. In the world of heterogeneous communication technologies, choosing the optimal one is a challenge for system architects, which is not an easy task often. The paper presents a comparative analysis of widespread communication technologies in the domain of IoT, and the conclusions presented based on the performed analysis, provide a better insight into the choice of the optimal solution depending on the problem domain and therefore better quality of solutions based on the concept of IoT.'),
(3431, 0, 0, 3, 'RSS-1', '2020', 1, 1, 'Dragoljub Krneta', 1, 'Data Vault as a Decision Support Platform for an Electricity Supplier in the Open Electricity Market', 'Data warehouse, Data Vault, supply of electricity, electricity market', 'The paper presents an approach to design data warehouse based on Data Vault concept in the supply of the electricity market. The Data Vault model makes improvements to data warehousing concept, namely scalability, flexibility and increased performance on data loads in a way that is not possible with traditional enterprise data warehouses. The motivation for the approach was to extend such benefits of using Data Vault for decision support in the open electricity market.'),
(3432, 0, 0, 6, 'STS', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Radio emission signal analysis – modulation recognition using deep learning technique', 'Deep learning, modulation, image processing, classification', 'This paper presents the overview of the modulation database creation, acquired data processing and modulation recognition model developing using a deep learning technique. Database is populated with real time generated, differently modulated radio emissions which partially occupy the frequency band from 15 to 55 MHz. The reference spectrograms of those emissions are the 300-time sample representations of the power distribution over the mentioned frequency band characterized with 500 data points. Those reference spectrograms are than used to train the deep learning model which provides the emission recognition capability. Image classification is achieved with the developed multiclass deep learning model which is meant to classify four types of radio emissions.'),
(3433, 0, 0, 2, 'STS', '2020', 1, 0, '', 0, 'Virtuelne privatne mreže (VPN) - analiza i softverska simulacija', 'VPN, IPSEC, Firewal, Cisco, procol, configuration', 'This paper presents Virtual Private Networks (VPNs). We analyzed the applications, pros and cons, categorization, configuration and security capabilities of VPNs. We offered definitions and theoretic explanations of VPNs, as well as the simulation of a VPN in order to analyze the security capabilities of the conducted experiment. The special attention is directed towards IP Security (IPSEC) and Firewall. The simulation of the secured network is realized using Cisco Packet Tracer simulation tool.'),
(3434, 0, 0, 4, 'STS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Ognjen Petrić', 1, 'SYSTEM FOR COLLECTING INFORMATION ON THE STATE OF THE PROCESS WITH SMS SUPPORT', 'SMS ; Beckhoff; PLC; TwinCat 2', 'The subject of this paper is the development of a device that will be able to control and manage the operation of an industrial process through a GSM network. This device should satisfy two basic requirements, i.e. to inform the user when the process attain a reference value, and that there is a possibility that the user can at any time check the current process values.'),
(3435, 0, 0, 3, 'STS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Zinaid Kapić', 1, 'Implementation of the genetic algorithm in an application for solving a traveling salesman problem', 'Traveling salesman problem, Genetic algorithm, Application', 'The theme of this paper is the implementation of a genetic algorithm in an application that solves the problem of a traveling salesman. The problem for the traveling salesman is the problem of finding the optimal route and returning to the point of origin. Since this problem belongs to the category of NP-difficult problems and is of factorial complexity, it does not use traditional methods but rather heuristic methods that derive their logic from the behavior of nature and natural processes. A genetic algorithm is a heuristic method whose logic is based on the biological process of evolution. This paper first describes the travelling salesman problem and the genetic algorithm, and then presents an application that uses the aforementioned problem for finding an optimal route for tourists, based on the PHP and JavaScript programming languages, and uses Laravel as an environment.');
