(3436, 0, 0, 5, 'STS', '2020', 0, 0, '', 0, 'Developments in Onboard Vehicle Systems', 'transportation industry, autopilot, navigation, remote software, automation', 'The transportation industry has been quietly undergoing a revolution, merging the capabilities of the fields of artificial intelligence, cloud computing and the Internet of Things to gain a resurgence in the fields of human endeavour and develop technology that is at the cusp of complete automation. The autopilot systems, navigation, intra-vehicular control units and remote software updates are some of the areas that have  been explored. Some of the challenges that are facing the industry are also explained, with possible paths forward as a closing note.'),
(3437, 0, 0, 5, 'STS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mihajlo Obrenović', 1, 'Širinsko impulsni modulator sa 555 tajmerom i strujnim izvorom', 'širinsko impulsna modulacija, 555 tajmer, faktor ispune', 'Sažetak — U ovom radu govoriće se o širinsko impulsnoj modulaciji (ŠIM). Pored primjene u energetskoj elektronici širinsko impulsna modulacija se može koristiti i za prenos informacija. Pojavom digitalizacije u upotrebi je sve češči prenos digitalnih signala. Širinsko impulsni modulator je sklop koji ulazni analogni napon transformiše u povorku impulsa kontantne frekvencije i promjenjivog faktora ispune.  Cilj rada je opisati jedan širinsko impulsni modulator koji koristi 555 tajmer i strujni izvor. Strujni izvor služi za generisanje konstatne struje kojom se puni kondenzator pri čemu se kreirea testerasti napon koji se poredi sa analognim naponom koji treba da se pretvori u povorku impulsa.  Analogni signal čije vrijednosti mogu da budu između 0 i 4 V, pretvaraju se u povorku impusla amplitude 5 V i faktora ispune između 10 i 90%. Za napajanje ovog sklopa koristi se 5 V DC napona.'),
(3438, 0, 0, 1, 'STS', '2020', 1, 1, 'Mirza Delibašić', 1, 'Some Improvements of the Parallel Karatsuba Algorithm', 'Long integer multiplication, Karatsuba algorithm, OpenMP', 'Multiplying long integers is one of the basic mathematical operations used mostly in cryptography.\r\nThe topic of this paper is experimental testing of different implementations of the Karatsuba algorithm for multiplying long integers using shared memory parallel programming.\r\nDifferent ways of using OpenMP were considered for optimizing implementations of the algorithm and the experiment results were analysed and compared.\r\nThe parallel implementation has achieved a significant speedup compared to the sequential code, with the maximum achieved speedup of 9 on a 12 core CPU.'),
(3439, 0, 0, 5, 'SUP', '2020', 1, 1, 'Radomir Jankovic', 1, 'Pristup мodelovanju nesavršenosti informacionog sistema u simulatorima vojnih sistema rojenja', 'modelovanje; komandno-informacioni sistem; nesavršenost; simulator; rojenje; sinhronizovani raketni udar', 'Predstavlja se pristup modelovanju nesavršenosti komandno-informacionog sistema u okviru simulatora vojnih sistema koji primenjuju ofanzivnu odbrambenu taktiku rojenja, kombinovanu sa sinhronizovanim raketnim udarom.  Nesavršenost informacionog sistema nastaje usled povremenih izostanaka informacije o stvarnom položaju pretnje, što može rezultovati paralaksom sistema i nepravovremnim raketnim udarom, ili čak njegovim izostankom. Uvođenjem nesavršenosti informacionog sistema, ovakvi simulatori dobijaju na realnosti, pa postaju korisniji za procenu mogućnosti odbrane ćelije teritorije od naoružane aktivne pretnje.'),
(3440, 0, 0, 1, 'SUP', '2020', 1, 1, 'Zvonko Radosavljević', 1, 'IMMPDAF Approach for L-Band Radar Multiple Target Tracking', 'multiple target tracking; radar;signal processing;', 'The interacting multiple model (IMM) and\r\nprobabilistic data association (PDA) filter (IMMPDAF), is\r\ndeveloped to support the air surveillance of the Track While Scan\r\n(TWS) radar systems. Take advantage of both, IMM and PDA\r\nalgorithms to increase the tracking efficiency of fast maneuvers\r\ntargets. The known algorithm was implemented in a radar\r\ntracking application for the purpose of modernizing the ‘C’ band\r\nradar, as a replacement for the conventional NN (Nearest\r\nNeighbor) algorithm which proved to be ineffective in situations\r\nwith airborne targets in the air. In extensive experiments with\r\ncomplex, target maneuver and non-maneuver scenarios has been\r\nshown that proposed algorithm to have robust tracking\r\ncharacteristics with small position and velocity error.'),
(3441, 0, 0, 3, 'SUP', '2020', 1, 1, 'Naser Prljaca', 1, 'An Implementation and Evaluation of Fast Embedded Model Predictive Control', 'model predictive control; embedded system;  hardware-in-the-loop', 'This work studies hardware and software aspects concerning the implementation and the performance evaluation of a fast real-time embedded Model Predictive Control  (MPC).  This study is  carried out using a  low cost and a low  power off–the-shelf high performance embedded computing platform (ARM Cortex M) and an off-the-shelf generic embedded MPC software implementation, with a general purpose QP (quadratic programming)   solver (MATLAB) . As an example, two oscillating masses system subject to input and output constraints is used.  Throughout  MPC  evaluation is done using a hardware-in-the-loop (HIL) experiments, achieving  a couple of  milliseconds sampling rates.'),
(3442, 1, 0, 10, 'P-3', '2020', 1, 1, 'Stevan Stankovski', 1, 'Using micro/mini PLC-PAC in the Edge Computing Architecture', 'PLC, PAC, Edge/Fog Computing', 'Programmable logic controller (PLC) are the core of any industrial automation. Many years, PLC are used mostly to solve logical control tasks. Increasing processor performance and memory capacity, PLCs have the ability to handle a number of different and more complex tasks that are no longer just logical type. This kind of controller is call Programmable Automation Controller (PAC). In industrial control systems are present different kind of architecture and concepts for integration in an enterprise information systems.  Edge computing architecture is one of them. In this paper is described comparison of performance some of micro/mini PLC-PAC in order to find how of micro/mini PLC-PAC can fit in the Edge Computing Architecture.'),
(3443, 1, 0, 12, 'P-2', '2020', 1, 1, 'Stevan Stankovski', 1, 'The Impact of Edge Computing on Industrial Automation', 'Edge computing, Industrial Automation, Fog Computing, Cloud Computing', 'Increasing the performance of all computing components enables the development of new architectures and platforms for data processing, sharing, distribution and storage of data. Speed, security and reliability of data transmission are essential parameters in industrial automation and therefore only those architectures/concepts that successfully meet these parameters have a chance to succeed in an industrial environment. General need for data sharing has made that the amount of data which generated and recorded significantly increased and therefore new approaches are needed to address to these facts, especially in industrial automation. One of approach in industrial automation is using Edge computing. Edge computing brings new power in data processing in industrial automation and opportunities in data processing of big data in real time. In this paper are described basics of Edge computing and its connections in industrial automation.'),
(3444, 0, 0, 6, 'SUP', '2020', 1, 1, 'Alem Komić', 1, 'DC motor dynamics data acquisition, parameters estimation and implementation of cascade control', 'DC Motor, Cascade control, Parameters estimation', 'This paper presents parameters estimation for Direct Current motor (DC) and implementation of cascade control of given Direct Current motor. The paper includes basic Direct Current Motor theory, Direct Current motor dynamics data acquisition, parameters estimation and finally analysis and implementation of cascade control.'),
(3445, 0, 0, 2, 'SUP', '2020', 1, 1, 'Milan Božić', 1, 'ADVANTAGES OF COMBINATION OF PD AND PID CONTROLLER OVER PID CONTROLLER IN THE EXAMPLE OF QUADCOPTER CONTROL AND STABILIZATION', 'Quadcopter; PID regulation; PD regulation;', 'This paper presents the problem of control and stabilization of a quadcopter and one of the solutions for improving the classical PID controller using a combination of PID and PD controller. An algorithm for implementing a PID controller with the ability to switch off the integral effect of the controller during operation is given. The results were obtained in simulations and then experimentally by testing on the OROZ (quadcopter) development system and comparisons of the first and second management methods were given.'),
(3446, 0, 0, 7, 'SUP', '2020', 1, 1, 'Nenad Popović', 1, 'Electrogastrogram and electrocardiogram interference: Application of fractional order calculus and Savitzky-Golay filter for biosignals segregation', '110', 'We present a combination of fractional calculus and Savitzky-Golay filter for extraction of both electrogastrogram and pulse rate signal from a mixed signal recorded with high sampling frequency (1 kHz). In order to evaluate the proposed method, we generated semi-synthetic biosignal mixture. After the method was applied, signal-to-noise ratio was calculated for the resulting signals. Obtained results suggest that there are benefits from the combination of Savitzky-Golay filter and fractional order calculus, compared to the usage of only one of those methods. Further examination will be performed on in vivo recorded signals.'),
(3447, 0, 0, 6, 'SUP', '2020', 1, 1, 'Petar Matić', 1, 'Conic Section Representation of Operational Point Trajectories for IM IFOC Drive Under Constraints', 'conic section representation, induction motor drive, operational constraints, operational point trajectories', 'The paper analyses trajectories of Induction Motor (IM) Indirect Field Oriented Control (IFOC) drive under operational constraints by representing model equations as conic sections in dq plane. By this, operating point trajectory is created by calculating intersection points of drive limits (voltage, current and break down slip) or different control strategies, e.g. Maximum Torque Per Ampere (MTPA) strategy. The approach is illustrated by set of computer simulations and experiments on low voltage IM IFOC drive with MTPA strategy used in battery supplied electric vehicle.');
